\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Could I have your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Warren{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Is Green Cottage, Woolston Green. Staverton you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you're married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What year did you marry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 1928.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 At Rill - Farm, Buckfastleigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many years did you live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Sixteen years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 We - we moved to Newtake Farm, Staverton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That was in 1916?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you stay there until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, and - and beyond that. 'Til I was married. '28. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember why the family moved from Rill Farm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Because my father wanted a larger farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 One of each. One sister and one brother. And - the sister was - two years younger t
han myself and the brother six. So that worked out about two years and four years, between my - brother and - my brother and the sister in between.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you were the oldest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well approximately twenty-two to three, I worked it back from when he died you see. And if I was born in 1900 - I think he took the farm in about - 1898.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was just two years before you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. About that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He came from Western Farm, Totnes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He was a farmer before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, with his father. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 His father had been in the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In the farm at Western.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Farming had been in his family for generations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh generations, generations. Yes. Yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So he would have not had any other job before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he ever do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not - not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he remain a farmer until he died?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When did he die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 1952.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was a long time after you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How old was your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well she was two years younger than my father so she was twenty. I mean this is - you know, as - as near as I can work it out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 She came from - a house at Hoverton. Totnes, close to Totnes. And her people were farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did she have any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not that I - I don't know, I can't answer that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did she work on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, I think she just kept house and - helped with her mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And she didn't work after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Except - housekeeping. Naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did she have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not to my knowledge you see I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. His only trouble was was getting the work done that he had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose farming would be very long hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes. Daylight 'til dark. And - farming in those days was quite different than it i
s today, there was no tractors, it was all done with horses and hard work, you know, it was quite a different thing altogether. Which I don't think we'd better go into those sort of things now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many rooms were there in the house at Rill Farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh - twelve easily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were they living rooms and bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well there were two - two receptions room and - three kitchens. And - five, six bedrooms. And an attic above that with three more up there.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did anyone besides yourself and your parents live in the house, any relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well, you see, it was - it was - it was - it was done in those days to have a boy in the house which worked on the farm and he lived with the family. And also my mother had a help - to bring us up and
 bring up us children - sort of a governess help, that taught us until we got about seven before we went to school. And they lived with us in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would they live, in one of the spare rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. They had a room each you see. There was a room set aside which was called the boy's room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What sort of things would he do, a farm help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, help with cattle and everything, general farm work you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How old would he be when he first came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh they'd come along you 
know - at various ages when they left school and start, some stayed, others went but - we had one that stayed with - stayed with us until he got married and then he married and went on another farm - not far from Totnes. And I think he's still alive today
, I'm not quite sure, I think so. I'm not sure about that, but I - I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you must had the farm boy and the governess in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In the house, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Apart from that did your mother have anyone else to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. To come 
- a woman to come from one of the cottage daily to do the housework, help to do the washing every week. That woman started doing washing for our family - about - 1908 or 1909, and she did it for my brother who was in father's old farm, up to four years ag
o.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was the same woman all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Same woman, and her husband worked for my father from before he was married until he died - at Staverton village, not very long ago, nearly eighty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The husband just did farm work did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh y
es, he was a general farm man you see. He started off as a boy in the house you see. Then he married a local girl in Buckfastleigh. They went in a cottage, and when we moved from - the farm - at Buckfastleigh to the farm at Staverton, they went down there
 and they had a son with them, which also started when he left school and he's still working for my brother today. So that that family have been with - my family since about 1908, seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that a sort of general pattern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, yes,
 it was. Yes. Yes. Oh yes. It was. They - they followed on. Of course some left but - they were the stalwarts of doing work on the farm those men, that's what happened in nearly every family you see. They went on from year to year. But this is rather an e
x
ceptional case of this boy - I call him a boy, he's sixty-five now, he's going up to the Country Show in May to get his long service - certificate, for being the longest - member with one family. They do this every year at the Country Show. And he's going
 up this year to get his certificate. Which I suppose is an honour you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 This woman who came in to help with the house wouldn't live in, she'd live in one of the cottages would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, she lived in the cottage. But mind you've got the fir
st haven't you, that there was a woman in the house always. We'd got a governess and help with my mother with all - well the general housework you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The governess would also help with the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes - everything as well, yes, and - and as we kids became older she took us on as - and taught us our first lessons you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So she wasn't primarily a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. She was a general help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - actually we had two or three over the years an
d - I think - three of them, in any case came from Cornwall. And another one came from quite close here at Malvern which is just across towards Torquay from here, quite local. The others were not local, they came from Cornwall.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you had quite a few really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well, over the years, yes. You see they - they principally left to get married. So happened, they still did that then you know as they do now, you know. It's one of those things isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were they domestic servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, not as su
ch, they were called assistants. And that was their - that was their standing - they were known as assistants, you see, adverts in the paper that so and so wanted an assistant to help with children and general housework. And that was it. And they lived wi
th the family as the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they be quite young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes, about twentyish you know, like they are you see, and - as I say they - they all got married, one married a local man from here now, I know where she lives quite well, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they have to have any qualifications?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 None whatever. No. None whatever. None whatever. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say she looked after you children, what kind of hours would she work as a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well that was - that was agreement. You see - if she wanted
 a day off she had a day off, if she wanted a week off she had a week off, there was no fixed hours at all. She got up in the morning when you did and she went to bed when you did you see, and - she had a room to sit in when she wanted to, by herself, wel
l you could do that with a big house you see. But they principally liked to be with the family at night and sit round the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So they were very much one of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. And - it goes to show, we've kept contact with all of them. Unt
il they died or - gone - gone a long way away, they - they come back you know, it - it was almost -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was like having a relative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well almost, yes. Yes it was. And what pay they got I couldn't tell you. I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What age would they be governess to you 'til, did you go to the normal school when you were five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
We went to the normal school when we were seven. And then my sister and I had to walk - a mile and a half to catch a train at half past seven. And we arrived back at half past five at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So she'd be governess until you were seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 'Til - there - there was a lapse you see between my age and my brother who was six years younger you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have just the one governess yourself or did you experience one or two governesses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh we had - three. I only remember one - particularly, on my part but - I say, she was a Cornish person. I only remember one. And she married a farmer in the South Brent area, and I think he's still living - she's called Mrs Stone 
now and - Nelli we knew her as, and - I think she's still over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of work would she do around the house, you say you had somebody coming in anyway to help clean the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, well she got the meals and - you see, and looked after
 us kids. That was her job, take us out for walks perhaps and then - picnics and - down by the river and all this sort of thing you see. Had a nice life actually. Very nice life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh exceptionally well, of course we had our moments, you all do don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 She wasn't a sort of stiff governess type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
We had one we didn't like at all. She was a Miss somebody or other and went away as a Miss somebody, but she was between fifty and sixty. We didn't like her at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You hear some stories of Victorian households where the governess was a real terror, it wasn't like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. Oh no, no, no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did the governess call you and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3087458\charrsid2384185 Well they called us by our C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 hristian names, 
and they called my mother Mrs Warren and - my father was called master. He was looked upon as master by all the men and anybody that was connected with - yes. Yes, yes. But that was customary wasn't it in those days. The way they were addressed in - in co
untry districts I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was the washing done at home or was it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No - yes, yes, done at home. By this woman I mentioned to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Mend but not make. They'd mend but not make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would the clothes be new or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3087458\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would they be bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Principally at Totnes. Or Buckfastleigh. You know, neighbouring towns. You see, we went to Totnes market - with a horse and trap every Friday. And - to by groceries and anything required for the house. And it was an hour and a half's drive both ways.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was it a very big market?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Totnes - Totnes was quite a good county market on - on the Friday. And the cattle market was - on alternate T
uesdays - in those days. It's still - still in being there, Totnes you see. It's still in being, both those markets. Mind you have a weekly cattle market in Totnes now but the pannier market is much smaller than it used to be. It consists of stalls - with
 
- fruit and clothes and all this you know - that's changed quite a lot. You see, it was principally farm produce before. And it was taken in there and brought up by the shopkeepers in Paignton and Torquay for - for the trading in that part of the country.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you'd go to the markets in Totnes, there wouldn't be sort of chain stories or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh there wasn't then. When you went in - when you went in to the grocers at Totnes - which my mother did every Friday, gave her order. Paid for the lot sh
e'd had the week before. And the groceries were all wrapped up in a very neat parcel with very thick brown paper and - and white string and - a man took those groceries - to wherever your horse and trap were stabled for them. It was all put in for you.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you did the whole lot in Totnes rather than in Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3087458\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes, got a few o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
dd things in Buckfastleigh but Totnes was the main shopping centre for us in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd be partly self-sufficient in the sense of being on a farm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. All your own vegetables you see. But of course there were no deep freezes and not fridges you see, you had to get fresh meat every week. It had to be kept in a safe outside for - to keep it a bit fresh, but you had no - no fridges, no - no elec
tric, nothing at all. We just had lamps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
What about the cows and pigs, nowadays people kill a cow or a pig and put it in the deep freeze, would you buy the meat or kill it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh buy it, buy it, because you had nowhere to keep it. The only
 thing they used to do was put a pig in. And salt it. In a standard with brine, that was always done. There was always a standard full of pork. But nothing else, no sheep or - or cattle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How long would one pig last then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well that depends how
 many visitors you had. You know, we used to have about two a year. For a house of that size, and you've got to remember you'd got to feed this growing up lad, in addition to us. And the woman in the house in addition to my mother and father, and that wom
a
n that came wash - came working every day. She got her midday meal. And the men that came and did the work on the Sunday - morning, the milking, they'd come in and sit down to a breakfast of cold ham and eggs every Sunday morning before they went. So - wo
men actually had a lot more hard work to do in those days than they've got today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of hours would the cleaning woman work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh she used to come about - eight o'clock and go again about four. And she had about half a mile to walk to her cottage that was all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 At this time her husband was working on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. And he used to start at seven and finish at five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he get his meals as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 On a Sunday. They always had a meal on - breakfast on Sunday mornings. And high
 days and holidays, Boxing Days and Good Fridays, when they came you see which was extra. But they didn't want any extra money you see, all they wanted was food - and plenty of cider to drink. Yes, oh yes, that's what they did do. Oh yes. Yes. This man of
 ours would drink eight pints of cider a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 While he was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And your father didn't mind?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, he just gave it to them. It was a perk that was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did that affect their work standard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not a bit, th
ey worked better with it. I tell you, he lived until he was - well on the eighty mark, he died two or three years ago, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How about shoes or boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, same thing applies, they were bought in Totnes you see at the stores.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you get through many boots in a year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh well you see as - as one became older and worked on the farm you usually had your boots made. There was a man to make them, there was a man in - in every little village there was a cobbler. And he made suitabl
e boots which would keep out the water, and a pair of leggings to go with'em. And you'd get through about - a pair of them every two years. They weren't worn so much when it was nice dry weather, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3087458\charrsid2384185 for the winter - there were no W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ellingtons you know. Jus
t to kick on and kick off. Well I remember when they came in. But I can't tell you exactly the date now but I remember. Between the two wars I suppose. Yes. Between the two wars they became common.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were the boots very expensive in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. Just on a pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, yes, I suppose you would say he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of jobs would he help with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I mean to say for one thing it was always his duty to
 go and buy the meat. And he always carved. And if we were having friends he helped generally with - getting things ready for whatever meal we were going to have. It was more common in those days for people to come in the middle of the day for a meal. Bec
a
use they had to go back with - a pony or a bicycle or - some - means of transport you see where - especially in the winter when it - became dark there was only one way to get back, that was two candelabras in a trap or - carry a lantern in your hand. No s
treet lights or anything like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose safety first meant ......?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Nothing. Nothing. You had to get out the way if you saw anything coming, lie in the hedge.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he help with anything like cleaning or washing up or making fires or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would your mother or the cleaning lady do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. Yes, yes, they - they would do that amongst themselves. The only thing my father would have to do was to see that there were plenty of logs for the fires. That di
dn't say necessarily he did it himself but he managed it that one of the men did do that and there was always a big log box full of logs - in the kitchen for every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That was the principal form of fuel was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes, yes. And of course we had big open fire - hearths, where we used to put in a whole faggot of wood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many fireplaces would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Rill Farm is a very big place isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There was a big oven hearth in the outside kitchen as we called 
it, the big kitchen. And there was a range - in the next one, a big iron range. And there was - a fireplace in the - dining room as we knew it then and one in the drawing room and there was a fireplace in every bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have them lit every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well not all, no, no, no, whichever you room you were going to use you see and - normally we had our breakfast in the kitchen. There was a big kitchen table there where everybody sat down to and then - in the afternoon evening part you'd have tea
 in the dining room followed by supper and there'd be a fire in there, and you see there was a range fire every day, which kept the place warm. Well you'd got no other means of heating a big place like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would the fuel be for the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Coal. Yes. Coal. And - there were five entrance to the - entrances to the place to start with, so you can imagine the draught in those days. There's five entrances to that place up there. Yes, it was quite a big - old place. Big house, yes. You see that f
arm and that house - originally, prior to 1906 belonged to a - another owner altogether, and it was bought by the Bickerton Estate when he died. And he used to reside in part of that house. Before my father went there. And he used to live there and I thin
k that the farmer and his wife had to look after him, he was a bachelor. And then it was bought by the estate - for the Bickerton House you see, the whole of that area round there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So your father went up to Bigadon did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. Bigadon - the 
owner of Bigadon bought the farm. He bought Rill Farm you see. And then it went in with the Bigadon Estate. You see. Yes, it - and we was tenants you see - where - we children were invited there to a Christmas party at the - big mansion up there, and our 
respective parents went there to another party every Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So when was it part of the estate, from 1906 onwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. That's all I can remember, I mean probably it went on before that, but - I can remember from then when we got old enough to
 go we went. We all had a present and a Christmas tree. But had to walk home down across fields with a lantern you know. Well - there you are you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of people would be up at these Christmas parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 All the tenants of the Rill - of t
he estate, that's all. Only of the estate, you see. He had about eight farms belonging to the estate you see. And he - he lived in London. And he used to come down there periodically. I can remember the grandfather, I mean - the - the - the generation tha
t
 I know are - are the owners of what the - I don't think they've got any left here now, I think they sold the lot, they live in London but - there was - there a son and a daughter the same age as my sister and my self, you see, and - we knew their grandfa
ther, when they were kids, and then we knew their father who was really the landlord as far as we were concerned. And then he left and went to London again you see and - that was it. Then the estate was sold up for death duties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often would he come down, just now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh - he'd be down perhaps two or three months in the summer, and he maybe - he always came for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So he was the host when you went up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes oh yes, he was the host. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did your father find him, did he get on O.K. with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well he - as landlords go, yes, I suppose he was - he was about average, he - he never spent any money on - on - on the farms in any shape or form, they - they simply wanted the rent and of course rents were
n't - a big lot of money in those days compared to what they are today. And - they held it for shooting and - and all this business you see, they used to have shooting parties there and all this.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he have to arrange them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. He did that all
 himself. He had two 'keepers you see. And a couple of - couple of people looking after his horses and his carriage and pairs and - etcetera, etcetera.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They wouldn't get in the way of the produce?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, but you see in those days when - when a man 
took a farm he realized that the landlord was going to - you see, they - the landlord reserves the right o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3087458\charrsid2384185 f the game. And - any - any shoo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ting on the state, you see, that is - that is in your agreement when you take the farm, you know the terms. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of game would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh pheasants and partridges you see and get some wild duck there, woodcock, snipe. In winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did all the people come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh friends of his. I - I - I wouldn't know but we used to be invited as kid
s when we got old enough to go and drive the pheasants out of the woods for them to shoot 'em. Oh yes. That's - that's done now. That's done now, on some of the estates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they ever have any fox hunts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you allowed to take part in them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well - not so much, then my father was always keen - on hunting, and he supported - the local hunt. And - since that I've supported it until last year, I've been connected with it since 1912, I attended
 my first meet of the hounds out of Bellafort Hall in the middle of Dartmoor. I had to ride a horse out there leaving home at eight o'clock, for my father to come out and ride all day and hunt and then I had to ride it back again. Getting home about nine 
o'clock at night. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would you get the horse from, from your own farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. That was part of your life you see. That was a day's holiday - for u
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd be twelve then wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Eleven or twelve, yes, that's the first time I - rode right out there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of day was it, was it a holiday, you say it was a holiday for you, was it during a school holiday or Boxing Day or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Now I don't know about that, I - I can't remember that but I do remember, you se
e, they used to have what they called a hunt week, and there'd be about dix - five or six different packs of hounds would come, and they would stay with - my father stayed out at Two Bridges with their hounds and horses and they'd - they'd meet - one day 
of the hunt week. And you see each hunt and the men that was invited would go and they'd have their day and they'd - they'd go and the next day the other lot would go out you see. It was a week - a recognized hunt week on Dartmoor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time of year would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well - this was in April. I remember when I had to ride back we had a snow storm and the road was white and it was the twelfth of April. Yes, snow in April. And I know I was d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 mn cold when I got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father ever help with things like decorating or repairs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well you see - there again that was the landlord's - liability. To - but that's what I've told you about this landlord, he wasn't keen on doing anything o
f that, and anything that we - my mother wanted done she had to employ somebody from outside to do the job for her. If he wanted a room - papered or - coloured whatever maybe, she - she had to get somebody to do it, the local - a local builder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did she have to pay the bill herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes. Of course some landlords do supply the materials and you've got to find the labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But there wasn't any redress on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he ever help with dressing or undressing you or bathing you, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not generally. No. No, that was the - help's job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Which help, the lady from the cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, no, the assistant - the assistant help, that was her job to look after us you see. With my mother but - my mother usually put
 us to bed. If she didn't she always came up to say goodnight. You know, that's gone on for generations hasn't it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, well you see there again it's - it's difficult to - to explain that. Y
es, of course he did you see - he may take me to market and nobody else with him. In the trap, and then again - he may take my mother out for an evening and we children were left home with the - person that looked after us. There wasn't any fixed rule abo
ut that at all but my mother never drove - a horse and trap. In her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did the governess ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
One did. Yes, one - used to be able to drive, I remember that. But - principally it was father's job to drive you know, he took it upon himself, that was his job you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would he go out for long walks with you or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, we used to walk every Sunday night all round the farm. Go out about six o'clock and get back about half past eight, that was Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many acres was the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Two hundred. And we had - in the winter we had to - walk to church every morning, leaving at - quarter to ten, into Buckfastleigh, up over the hundred and ninety something steps. And back home by half past one. And my mother would never c
ook on a Sunday. Oh - never cook on a Sunday, it was an old Victorian - idea she had. She always said you mustn't do anything on the Sunday that you can do on any other day of the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would there be no cooking in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Except potat
oes, they were always boiled when we got back, but it was always the cold meat from what we had on Saturday, on Sunday. That was a recognised thing. With us. I don't know about other people. And - we had that meal and then we used to - in the winter we ha
d
 - after we'd had our tea we had to go and sit down or - or stand around the piano and sing hymns - until it was time to go to bed. We played cards occasionally but not on a Sunday. My mother wouldn't knit on a Sunday, she wouldn't do any mending on a Sun
day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would she tolerate anybody else doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
She didn't like it, she had to accept it as she got older but she didn't like it at all. No, it was against her - the way she was brought up you see. She was real Victorian you see, being born somewh
ere about 1830 or 1840. Something like that, you see. Well, yes, my grandfather started farming when he was eighteen. And - he - he lived until he was ninety-four. My grandmother was ninety. And - he lived in Totnes retired, opposite Bridgedown church. An
d he retired in 1914. '14. And he'd been in the farm for fifty-two years. So work it back from there will tell you when he started.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you were living in Rill Farm you wouldn't have your grandparents with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He wasn't with us but we used to 
go and see him. See, we had our set - visits to make around Christmas. You visited your uncles and aunts and - on - on special days. Boxing Day. Christmas Day was always spent home with the family, but Boxing Day we went here and - the next day somebody c
ame to us and so it went on, for about a week. Well yes, but that was it you see. As I say, principally - to midday meal. Because - having to get back you see, yes, because you weren't home then perhaps 'til nine o'clock you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you'd got to get the children to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well exactly, and you had to go all through those lanes that you lost yourself in today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of thing did he read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well - books, you know, general - according t
o our age. And my mother read to us more than my father did. And the governess usually told us stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Bedtime stories, you know, usual - the usual things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would she teach you during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh the way - the principal thing was in those days to - to learn the way to write. And to read and to spell. Those were the three things that they were keen on before you went to school you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So by the time you were seven you could do all three of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, you could - you had book - copy books for writing in those days, and you copied the writing - you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did the stories have a religious flavour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not altogether, no, no, some of them did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother tell you stories as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would there be any difference between the stories that you got from your governess and from your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well actually, I - I - I wouldn't like to commit - it's rather difficult to remember that. But I know we used 
to look forward to hear the stories, and we used to - we had a book that they used to read to us when we went to bed. We slept in separate rooms you see, so she had to go around. Naturally - naturally the younger one went to bed earlier.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did she get her stories from, did she get them from books or from local stories around the area or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I think she got them from books, from children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 s books you see. Before you were old enough to read and understand, after you could read your own storybook you didn't want to be told a story.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you get fairy stories and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father ever tell you any stories at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, not a lot. Not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He was mainly the one who read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he ever look after you when your mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Well he - he - he had to I mean and that was it. But - it was very unusual for my mother to be out without my father because you've got to remember there was only one way to go, by t
rap, horse and trap, you see, you'd got to walk a mile and a half to get - well, near - practically a mile and a half to Buckfastleigh even, that was the closest little - town - of any, well she wouldn't naturally walk a lot like that. She used to go some
times in the afternoon and take us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would your mother and father ever go out together and leave you with the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes, yes, yes, whenever they'd got - a party or whatever they were going to, you see, and - we used to be taken to To
rqay, pantomime - once a year. And if we went to Piagnton on the beach once a year that was a - a - a great day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you just go for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 A day, once a year and then you looked forward to it. Well then you - again you had to get there with a pony and trap you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You wouldn't get the train from Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well you could to Totnes, but then you see to get to Paignton you had to go up all around Newton Abbot to go down the other side, whereas with the pony and trap - just abo
ut threequarters of a mile from Totnes to Paignton and you were there. We used to put the - the - the pony and trap in a - in - in a dairyman's stable just on the outskirts of Paignton and walk in. And my father's seen all the buildings below the level cr
ossing at Paignton in his lifetime, that was all marshes when he was a boy. He's seen all that built. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 During those years it was just about the time the seaside was becoming popular wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It wasn't until the late nineteenth century that people bothered to go to the seaside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh no. No. But that was our - annual trip. To Paignton. But of course as we got older I mean that became more frequent, well - you know what it's like now. But nobody visit you today - not like we did. Not like we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you go on these Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. We never went to Sunday school. No. Never went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that because of the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose so. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have any tasks yourself that you had to carry out regularly at home when you were very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, after you came home from school even, we didn't get back until, as I tell you - five o'clock, half past five, well I had my duty to do helping my father outside. Do anything that want
ed doing. The pony to be seen to. Calves to have their food given to them. Take the cows out when they were milked and put them up in the field, you had your jobs, and we had jobs to do before we went in the morning at half past seven.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever do any milking of the cows and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. But not regularly until we left school. What we did was more or less our own idea, but you see - that was it, we - we had nothing else to do. And that's how we became so interested in farming be
cause we were brought right up - right up to it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was your sister the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh she was just the same. Yes, exactly the same. She went out as I did. But my brother was more fortunate, he got sent off to a public school and - he never did very much home - until he'd left school. You see, being the third one he - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was he the middle one or the youngest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, he was the third one. My sister was the middle one. My sister's still living with my brother in a farm down here now where 
my father was. Just down - in this valley, it's only about a - a mile from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So he came back from public school and became a farmer as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Actually he went away - and went to Wales and he had a farm over there to do with 
the Nuffield Trust. And - managing this farm for him, well when my father became ill - and - couldn't carry on with the farm he lived about twelve months after he became ill, he was a diabetic and - when he got beyond looking after the farm my brother cam
e
 home and took the farm on from then. That was about 1950 you see. He died in '52. He came home with his wife and two daughters. And he's still in the farm where my father was when he went there in 1916. And now my sister is there living with him, she nev
er married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you ever help your mother around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, if there was anything to be done, if she - they wanted some logs - to be brought in or if they wanted - anything, you go out and get some apples, get what you want, go out in the garden and get this, get that you see, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was very much give and take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Absolutely. No hard and fast rules at all. If you didn't want to do it you kept out of sight you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How long did you do these jobs, until you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. And then I came home and worked on the farm with my father you see. Right up 'til when I - went in the services in 1917.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When did you leave school then, in about '14 or '15?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 '15. '15, yes. I went to Totnes Grammar School. And the who
le school consisted of sixty-two boys. That was - considered a record, sixty-two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That was a lot of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. I was there - when I was in the first class there were eight boys. And I've got a photo of 'em all now and there's
 some of 'em are still living. Yes. They're all around here, Totnes. Mind you, this was a grammar school where you had to pay in those days you see, there was no - I was there when the scholarship was introduced. And the scholarship boys started coming. I
t altered from when I started as - as - as the years went on you see. It was beginning to get - when it was an opportunity for people - that had got the brains to go there on a scholarship-basis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you didn't go there 'til you were seven years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You went straight to grammar school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, before that I went to a mixed school at Totnes. A kindergarten, with boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that fee paying as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. And that was run by - an aunt of my mother's. A littl
e kindergarten school. In point of fact it was quite a large kindergarten school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I should say - a hundred easily. Boys and girls. And that was right opposite the grammar school in the main street. So - you see - you 
see, at Totnes - at -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How would you get to Totnes, on the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, I told you. We had to go - I told you earlier on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But you'd go first of all initially wouldn't you being the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Actually I stayed in Totnes - with an a
unt of mine, my mother's sisters, for about two years, and stayed there all the week and went home on Fridays when they came into market and went in on the train again - on Monday morning until we got about eight or nine. Then my sister came along, to go,
 
and we went together by train, you see. That - that's how that worked. And then she stayed on there until she was - eleven or twelve and then she went to a school in Plymouth. A private school down in Plymouth. At - I forget the name of the place. Torring
ton Place it was, the school, I forget what they called the school. It was a -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say she was at the kindergarten for all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Oh yes, the girls went on there until they were twelve or thirteen you know. And then - then they went off
 just sort of a finishing school you see. As they've got today you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How long would the finishing school go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well they could stay as long as they liked you see it depends what they were going to do, if they were going to study to beco
me teachers or any profession at all they could stay on and take exams. But my sister - did - didn't do that, when she - when she got - sixteen I expect, around there, she came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things did you do in the kindergarten, did your brother ever go to the kindergarten or did he go straight to public school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, he went to kindergarten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would you do in the kindergarten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well just ordinary lessons, reading and writing and - and they had a little - you know,
 they used to do these little plays and all this the same as they do in other schools you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was like a private school almost?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, more or less, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did all the children come from around Totnes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was Buckfastleigh considered a long way to go to the kindergarten or was it the only one available?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
The only one available, there was nothing at Buckfastleigh except the ordinary - what they used to call the council school in those days, which is still there but of course now it's classed - much larger of course. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of hours would it be at the boarding school - the kindergarten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh only from nine - nine to four. Full day you know, and a break - and we had to take our meals with us you see
. Sandwiches. There was no meals or anything of that, go out and buy a bun. You could get a lot of a penny then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you expected to stay inside the school premises?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, you could go out in the hour - the - the break in the midday, 
from - I forget - half past twelve to half past one, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You weren't having to keep in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh no, not unless you'd misbehaved yourself and then you may not be allowed out for a week. They were very strict you know. Oh yes. Oh yes. 
Oh yes they were very strict. And they were principally - middle aged people that were teachers, they weren't young people like they've got today. They were middle aged people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you be met by your aunt at the end of the day, the one you stayed with at Totnes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well that actually was at - that was adjoining where the school was so that - that - it was my mother's relations you see and they had this house, and my uncle was - he was in partnership with another man, there was a brewery in Totnes 
in those days and he was a partner in this brewery up at the top of the town now. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you'd be able to find your way to the school and back on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, we had to go out to the station you see and get the train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I mean when you were staying in Totnes during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well it was next door. It was next door you see. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would be on it then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh several - school - twenty schoolchildren, some got off at Staverton, some got off at - Buckfastleigh and some 
went through to Ashburton, 'cos there was another grammar school at Ashburton. In the St Lawrence's chapel. That took all the people from that side you see. But - we went to Totnes, because I think of my aunt being there. Yes, you see it was convenient I 
think - that was the reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have to wear a uniform at the kindergarten?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever have to wear special clothes at home while you were being taught by the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. But we used to wear stiff collars you know. With a tie. And a dark coat, I mean, it - wasn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid338851\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 a uniform as such. Yes. Oh yes, you were tidy you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was there much emphasis put on things like tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes, if you went in with very dirty boots they'd want to know why you cam
e with dirty boots. Well we used to change our boots when we got there because we - I told you before, we'd got to walk - mile and a half to the station in - the sort of weather we've been having lately and what you've experienced you know what they were 
like. There was mud under the soles. As I tell you no Wellington boots just to kick off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 At the kindergarten or before that the governess or your mother, did they emphasise certain things in life, like duty and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well they tried to impress 
on you you see the main thing that - we found - more so at the grammar school than at the kindergarten, but it applied in the kindergarten to a certain extent, but of course you weren't very old, not - the main thing - you were put on your honour - at the
 
grammar school. And you were expected not to - do things that you'd been told - they didn't want you to do. You see, you had to wear your cap with a badge on it. And they didn't expect you to go out in the street without that. If you went out into the pla
ying field or in school that was all right, but they expected to see you come in and go out with your cap on with the badge on it. And you had a blazer you see for the summer and - that was the same as there is today, there was - that was a - there was a 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 blazer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185  for the cricket team and - and the football team.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was there much sports in the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. They've got the field now, same field there down by the station. They still -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they lay any special emphasis on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Ye
s. There was football you see every Wednesday afternoon and every Saturday, because we had to go to school Saturday mornings in those days you know. Oh yes, you went home midday on Wednesday and you had to go in Saturday morning, go home again midday Satu
rday. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 By the time you were at the grammar school you were going there and back each day were you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Or were you still living with the aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, no, no, after about - well ten I expect, I - eight to ten I - I traveled by train for the rest of my schooldays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was only perhaps the first year that you were living with your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Two years. About two years, yes. Yes. Yes. And - the person that looked after me there, and my sister - a cousin you see of mine
 and - she looked after us children, that was her job, her father was an invalid - towards the end of his life. And - she used to look after us, and she's still living, in a flat down at Torqya. She's about eighty-five. Never married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They seem to live long round here don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. I don't know what it is. Contented minds. Yes, she's still there, we went and - went to see her now only last week. She's got a nice flat down Torqyay overlooking the sea. And - she's crippled up a bit with rheumati
sm but then we all get like that. This - that's one thing we do get in this part of the country, damned rheumatism. I've got it myself, muscular. There you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 With the governess, kindergarten and grammar school, what would happen in each case if you
 did something that the teacher or governess disapproved of, were they very different experiences or in each case would they be strict with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well you see when you had a governess if you'd really misbehaved yourself you were sent to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would send you, the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
She would. Oh yes, she would. She'd tell my mother what you'd done so and so wrong and - she suggested you be sent to bed. My mother would say, well if - Miss So and so says so - whatever she was called - you - you'd got to go bed and that's it. See?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would you do wrong that caused that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, I - I - I wouldn't know. I - I should get - something you shouldn't do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever feel you were sent to bed without being too guilty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, I mean it's difficult to explain that. You may have been a naughty boy for some reason, I - I couldn't - couldn't quite remember that.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember being punished at the kindergarten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, of course, 'cos the boys used to fight the
 girls. That was one of the things. The main things that went wrong there and then - you got in trouble, you were kept in or you had to write a hundred lines or you had to do something, and the same applied at the grammar school. Of course if you were rea
lly - really bad at the grammar school you had the cane. Common thing. All the school was assembled in the school hall and - the - the headmaster would give a boy a - a dozen whacks and that was it. And they took it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In front of the whole school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. And they took it. But it had to be pretty - a pretty bad thing, you know, to have to have the cane, but - it was done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was it just the headmaster who did the caning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say there were only sixty-two boys, how many teachers would there be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well we had the first - there was a - there was a teacher for every - every - every form you see and so much - we had a physics master, and we had a sports master, and we had the - the - the - the - number of the - number one, the botto
m class, the first class master you see. And there was the head and the deputy. But as I say - it began to grow terrifically from when I went. When I lect there was quite a number there then you know, and it's grown ever since as you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you had a wide range of subjects really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. You see the sports}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 master used to do the gymnasium, we had gymnasium once a week. And physics you see and - and - science master and all that. They - they had 'em all. And - some of them lived in the scho
ol house with the headmaster and his wife, others lived out privately with their families you see. And in many cases their boys even went to the school. They - they were there with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would these teachers be drawn from, would they be local men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No, I - I don't know, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they all be men in the boys grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. I had a cousin that was a master there. And he - he qualified at Cambridge and came there as a master but - he didn't stay there long, he went abroad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about the pupils, were they all from farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh all - all professional - people of Totnes you see - and the - and some from Paignton. They were - I mean - and even people with shops you see, it was open for anybody that liked to pay,
 they could send their - children there, there was no restriction on that in any shape or form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of comparison would there be between the fees for a grammar school and the fees for a public school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I wouldn't know. I wouldn't know. Didn't know what they had to pay. Not like it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember when the scholarship came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you still at school when it happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Yes. The boys started coming when they'd got scholarships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would they come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Locally and Paignton, you see, several came from Paignton, Southbanks you see and all round - covered a big area you see. There was nothing between that and Plumpton grammar school you see and Ashburton the other side and Newton Abbot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they have any sort of boarders at Totnes grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. 'h yes. Oh yes. Yes. Then you see we - the football teams used to play - at the grammar schools - around in the area you see, there was Mountpeliers at Paignton which was - well, on the same par in those days as a grammar school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say there were sixty-two of you, what proportion of those boys would be boarding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Eight or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not many then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, no, no, eight or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did you think of this school, did you like both the kindergarten and grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
I never liked school at all. Really. But - I'm sure that it gave one a good background, and I often think of - the things that we were told to do and not to do, which they've been a great
 benefit as you've gone through life, I'm sure of that. And I say the main thing being you were put on your honour. You see, and - if you didn't - carry that out you were in - bad trouble, because they told you that you'd break - broken a tradition of the
 school, that was the tradition, that meant you were - you were not allowed to do that you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did many people break their honour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. You'd get bad ones as you do now. We had an awful man, two awful fellows in there, but that's all right, they've done quite well since.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would there be any instances where there'd be boys left out on their own, they were sort of ostracized by the rest of the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 If they did they soon came around because you see there were not enough of you to do that
 and you were all too - closely - mixed up in - in private life as well as you were in school life. You see, we went to parties - I mean - you see, it was - it was more of a - yes, it was community of it's own you see, it was quite a different thing those
 
days than - you see, we knew practically - the parents of all the kids that were there. Not quite, but - within reason in your own age group you knew them all you see. And - we had our party this week and they had theirs next week you see and most of the 
schoolboys were there. That's how it was you see, and some of the girls from the kindergarten the other side, when they got older you see, because you - you'd been brought up with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 This would apply both at the kindergarten and the grammar school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Yes. I went to a celebration of the golden wedding a fortnight ago - of a girl that started school in the same class as I did in 1908. So you see, I mean, that - that - oh yes, oh yes, you see. But you know the - we mustn't mention names on t
his I know, but you know the big - the big farm at Totnes don't you, we won't mention their names, well - they both went to school with me. And I see them now, we're quite friendly. I mean - they've gone their way and I've gone mine but we still - you kno
w, have a good old chew about old - good old days. And not only them but others around in the district you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have your midday meal at school at the grammar school or would it be the same as the kindergarten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was optional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There was an actual midday meal available?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
You had to go into the schoolhouse and go into the dining room with the headmaster and his wife and all those that were having the meal. It was optional. And you had to pay for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That was an extra. I used to go in occasionally, not always. It was - as I say, it was optional.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would you do otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Take sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of thing would you have in your sandwiches?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, meat of some sort. Pastie. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Homemade pastie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. It wouldn't - it wouldn't be bought, it would be stuff that mother had made - in the house, and we'd taken it with us you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did you feel about the teachers? Did you have any favourite teachers, both gr
ammar school and the kindergarten? Any one you can remember particularly for good or bad reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well of course some of the teachers we liked more than others. We were always very fond of our first teacher in the - in the number one form because he 
took us on, you might say when we started going there. We were always more - more fond of him than any of the others because of the - he - he started us off on the whole thing you see. We had one very strict teacher which the boys used to - pull a bit off
 but he was forgiven for everything because he was a wonderful cricketer. Exactly you see, that was our - our idea you see, because he was a good cricketer we would forgive him for all the things that he did to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did he teach normally, did the form master do a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Except the physics master.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have a laboratory and things like that at the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes. And a lovely gymnasium.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When was Totnes grammar school built?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh sixteen hundred and something. Up over the door in Totnes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did the teachers expect you to speak in a certain way, were you supposed to be a gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, no, no, you were accepted as you were, you were told that you mustn't talk so b
road. So broad. You know, not broad Devonshire you see. And - there again you see a lot of people say to me that you're not Devonshire. I say well I was born and bred here anyway, but I think you see - by going to a school like that and having a governess
 
- from not in the immediate neighbourhood - one learnt to talk like they talked, which was rather different to the broad - I can give you a broad Devonshire as broad as you want it. If you want it. I can give it to you as broad as you want it but - then g
oing in the services you see again - you mixed with all - all walks of life there you see and - lost that very broad Devonshire. But I can give it to you if you want it. I can give it to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have to make an effort to speak properly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185  or was it j
ust sort of natural}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185  from learning it early on, being trained to speak properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
We found that when we were young - on the farm with the men we became - liable to use - a very broad Devonshire dialect. Which was not approved in the school. But it woul
d have been approved in the school at Buckfastleigh. You see, that - that's just that little difference you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did your father think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well he wasn't broad either, and my mother was far from broad, you see, she was brought up more or less 
in a town although she was at Hoverton, but her people were Totnes people, they weren't broad - speaking Devonshire people. You see - I mean I think again it's education, how you are. And you've got to - try and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Had your parents been to school before you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of school did they go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well my father went to a grammar school. And my mother went to this school at Totnes I expect, this - girls school. Although there was a kindergarten but there - it was a girls school
 right up to leaving age. Which I say was a relation of hers, the - the woman that ran the thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You mean the kindergarten that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It's separate from the girls. The kindergarten was mixed you see, but there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But when you got to a certain age, the girls went on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
We had to go off then, the boys were only - and the girls stayed, if they wanted to, in - in the same school but they were in the - girls school then, separate from the kindergarten. The kindergarten was mixed, but it wasn't mixed after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was on roughly the same premises though was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was on the same. Oh yes, yes. And it's still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes. You had - reports were studied very carefully. Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have homework and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. And they used to go in periodically to see the headmaster or headmistress whichever it was to know how you were getting on. What you were - god with and what you were bad with sort of - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What were your specialities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh I was just general average that's all. Nothing wonderful. Well you see, I'd got in my mind from the very start that I was going to become a farmer and the qui
cker I could get home on that farm and do some work the better I thought - which you had to do in those days. You see, it was the only way. I mean, I've taken three horses and double furrow plough and ploughed some fields and I can do it and you see, the 
- the advantage you had by being brought up in that line, when you employed men, if you could go out in the field where they were p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 oughing or what every they're doing and say, look, you're not doing this right you know, take over the thing yourself and say
, look that's how I want this done, and the men take notice of you. You see? That is the difference in now but of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
course I mean the whole thing has changed now, because of college trained and all this you see. But - when it comes down to brass tacks I mean farming today and farming when my father was farmer is quite a different thing altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you were still at home before you went to the kindergarten would you each have a individual session with the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, all together. But you
 must remember there was - six years difference. My brother didn't get as much from a governess as my sister and myself. You see, we were getting old then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did you call your governess in those days, would you call her anything special, nanny or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 By her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
hristian name. Yes, just by her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 hristian name, whatever it was you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did the hours increase with your governess as you grew older before you went to the kindergarten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No, she just did - perhaps a couple of hours i
n the morning and then an hour in the afternoon and then went out for a walk or - you know, whatever was doing. No hard and fast rules.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember at the kindergarten whether the girls had the same kind of punishment as the boys or was there a separate rule for girls?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No I don't think so, not in the kindergarten in any case. And of course at the grammar school it was all boys. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember whether the teachers at both schools now singled out certain children for different treatment from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They didn't sort of coach slowcoaches along?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, they were all treated on - on a level I mean - you see, we were in age groups.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many would there be in each class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I - well I - I forget, I - I don't know, I - I can't remember. - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Sixteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have liked to have stayed on longer if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No, because my ambition was to go home 
and be on the farm, that was my life as I - you know, at that time, but then of course the war came along and - I - I - I volunteered and went in the army when I was seventeen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you only did a full year on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That's all. Yes. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever go to anything like evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you have any regrets about your education at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not really. Except that as I - as I previously told you - being the older member of the family we were expected to go on
to the farm and help the family. Whereas the next son - had an opportunity to go away to a boarding school. And had a better education. Whether that did him any good or not I don't know. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that the general rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well generally, yes. Yes.
 I suppose if I'd said, now look, I'm not going farming, well probably then I should have been given opportunity to take some further education, but my idea was to be home you see. To carry on you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did the idea of going to public school ever come up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, definitely, because as I told you before you had discipline and - you were taught - the right things to do and - and - and then you were encouraged not to do th
e wrong things, you know I mean - it was part of life wasn't it in the country you see and - no doubt going into Totnes, and staying with my aunt over the week - was a great benefit to me - in many ways. Because you see it got me out into - a wider - into
 
a wider - having wide - more friends and meeting people that I should never have met had I not gone into the town to - to spend part of my - earliest part of my schooldays, you see I made contacts. You see I played in the football team. And I played in th
e cricket team. Well had I had to go home every - half day, Wednesdays and Saturdays, there wouldn't have been an opportunity for that. But by being in there I got in involved you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How long did you say you stayed with your aunt for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh - well a couple of years, yes - I - I forget exactly you know, to the day, but about a couple of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You commuted when you were at Totnes grammar school though didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father ever bath you when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Not to my know - not that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember as an older child helping the younger ones with anything they found difficult?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, we used to help each other in all ways, I mean - we were a very united family, you know what 
I mean, one helps the other with - the oldest one always got the blame for everything but - that's part of life isn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you expected to look after the younger ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, not as - not as such but if they went out with you you - you felt y
ou were responsible for them. As I've told you we lived very close to the River Dart. And - we werenot allowed to go there on our own. Not - not - there were - there had to be two in any case. Even - when we were younger if we wanted to run off and you we
n
t to the river there'd soon be somebody coming to know where you were. And you could see the river from the house, it was no distance you see, but that was it - you didn't go to the river, and then I - got very friendly with a - a man that lived in a cott
age quite close who was a retired - bank man and he used to take me fishing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What age was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh - nine, ten, along then you know yes. Eight, nine or ten. We used to go down and get in a boat and pull across to the other side of the river becau
se there was better fish that side he said than there was the other, but that's not always the case isn't it, it's always better the other side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever do any salmon fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, that's what he did. That's what he did. Yes. And he used
 to catch quite a lot. But - that - that was - a lot of my growing up time in spare time was spent in that way, and then in the - in the winter, the - him and another - retired bank man lived quite close and they used to shoot rabbits and - we used to go 
out with them and ferrets and - oh yes, and bolt them from the hedges and shoot them you see. I mean rabbits were very plentiful in those days, they thought nothing to get twenty, twenty-five a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time of day would have to go out to get that many?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh they go out - no, they bolt 'em from the hedges you see, they put the ferrets and bolt them in the hedges out from their burrows you see, they weren't outside you had to get 'em out. And then they used to shoot 'em. And - they'd come and bring 
the rabbits in and chuck 'em down, take one perhaps for their ferret and they'd say, do what you like with them you see. Well they did it just for the fun of doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you say you had the hunts and the other shoots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. That was the
 main - the three main things around there was fishing, and - rabbits, and - and - and hunting, I mean that was the - and of course we had good races at Buckfastleigh in those days, it was a National Hunt course then you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Which one is that now, down towards Dene?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. But of course now it's - it's - it's not a hunt - not - a National Hunt anymore, it's just used for point-to-pointing now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often would they have races down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They used to have them at Whitsun. Once a year, yes. Now there are three point-to-points held there. In March, and April.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They still have them now do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes, but not under National Hunt, rules. Which is quite different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you ever taken out visiting neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Quite often. Quite often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 With whom would you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - that depended, mostly with mother you see if she was invited out to tea and bring the kids. And we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Just round the neighbourhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. And of course they - they again c
ame back to us you see. But - the - the - governess or whatever you like to call her, never - very rarely went with us on those occasions. We went with mother you see. There again, if it was any distance - oh yes, if it was any distance we had to be taken
 in a trap, we couldn't walk. You see, so that the - the visiting was very restricted except for as I told you before round the Christmas time when we went to relations in - quite a distance away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Then you'd have a week's holiday anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well no - yes, from school, but the farm would go on exactly the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The farm wouldn't have a sort of holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, no, no. Work has to bed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid338851\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 one - three hundred and sixty-five days a year, milking twice a day. And that's just the basic thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever go out with just your father at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, I told you I think didn't I. Probably he took me to market when I began to get a bit interested and - farm sales and things like that you see, all connected with with - with farming, there wasn't much else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever go shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, yes, you see, and we were picked up from the shops at Totnes when we stayed you see, as I told you, they went in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember any other outings with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I tol
d you we used to go to Paignton once a year. Which was a drive of an hour and a half. Spend the day on the beach and - back again, and we looked forward to that one day. It became - it became more as we got older, but that was - that was the beginning you
 see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What day would this be, in the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they have Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. August Bank Holiday. Same as we do now practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they take them though, being on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The men would you see. T
he men that worked on the farm would have their holidays then as they do - as they do now, but of course they didn't get a week's free holiday, with pay, or a fortnight, three weeks, whatever it is now. I mean that's quite new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they get paid for bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, that was a recognised thing, they were paid so much a week, and you see - I - I think I told you before, the men were - men were quite different in those days, it wasn't pay at all. They didn't think about that, i
t was the - it was a lot of perks they got you know - all sorts and sizes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever go away for a holiday as such?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 For any length of time? No. Except - yes, yes. The aunt and her daughter and so that I stayed with in Totnes - also us
ed to go to Teignmouth, for a month in the summer and - we kids in turn went there. But that was only on about two occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You went for the whole month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, we'd go for a week each. Yes, wouldn't all go together, no. That was away back - I 
can tell you the house in Teignmouth where we stayed. I - I could show you where the house is now. You know, those things stick don't they. Yes. I do remember that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did that end while you left school, was that while you were just children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well
 you see, I didn't have much time between after I left school and when I was in the services, only about eighteen months that was all. And then of course it was quite different you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father or mother ever go over to Teignmouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh ye
s. They'd go for the day, they'd go by train you see. They' could get a train from Buckfastleigh to Totnes and then main line to Teignmouth, oh yes. That was quite possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would you do on these holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well muck about on 
the sand like kids do, and make castle and watch them washed down or something like that you know. And of course the beaches were reasonably empty then those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You can't remember a family holiday as such, a week's holiday with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well - until we got - well perhaps six years old, we were expected to go to bed at - seven o'clock at the latest, 
even the oldest of the family. Then it got to eight as you got older but - when we were quite young it was six o'clock and that was it. We - we went to bed. No - no argument about it, you just went to bed and - whoever was helping my mother would see that
 you went to bed if she didn't herself which she very often did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
I - I don't know. Too early I expect. You usually want to do things before you - you always want to be older than you are don't you when you're growing up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you share the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, no, we had a separate room each.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Your mother and father had one room, the governess had one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. And the boy in the house had a room and we three kids had a room. I think m
y brother - had a bed in the same room as I was but my sister always had a room on her own. All right through, I never remember any other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And your brother would be away after a certain age wouldn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, 'cos he went to boarding school you see, he was just home for holidays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
We did not have a bathroom, we used to have a tin tub in the kitchen in front of the hearth fire. And the water had to be carried in from the next kitchenette - and - we used to 
have a good roaring fire in the hearth when the cold weather was and - that was it, there was no bathroom. And there was no indoor toilet. You had to walk - quite - thirty yards - from the door of the house to get to the toilet down the other end of the g
arden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When would you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Every week. Every week we reckoned to, yes, and bathed twice a week. Regular. But when we were small of course you were bathed e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 very night, you know, kids grow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ing up you see and - that was it. B
ut as we got older twice a week we used to reckon and change clothes on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Saturdays rather than Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, used to be Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Breakfast and dinner was - in the kitchen, and tea and supper in the dining room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And what time of day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh very - very regular hours, breakfast about eight. And the midday meal at one, and - cup of tea about four and supper about eight o'clock. But - the midday meal was the main meal. We called tha
t dinner. We didn't know anything about lunch until - lunch to us was when the men used to stop from - half past nine until ten o'clock to eat out beside the hedge, they were having their lunch. That was - of course that was how it was in those days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would be present at the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh, everybody. All the lot that were around.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would the farm assistant be there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Oh yes. But not in the evening two. Not tea and supper. They had that in the kitchen, given to them in the 
kitchen wherever they were you see. But they - they'd have midday meal and breakfast all together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about the assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, oh yes, yes. Yes, oh yes, they'd all be the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time of day would the meals be then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I told you. 
Eight o'clock. Eight o'clock. One o'clock, and - tea about four to half past and then - supper as we called it about seven to half past. But of course that didn't apply when you were young, you were gone - to bed, you see, but that's when they had their m
eals, the rest of the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you describe what sort of things you'd have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh, just the main plain things, you see, we had our own bacon and we had our own eggs. And it chiefly consisted of - of fried breakfast, eggs, bacon, per
haps - the - there were no tomatoes in those days but - hogs pudding or sausages, you know, similar to what we have today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What's hogs pudding, is that black pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, the only white hogs pudding which we used to - which we - which made you s
ee. They made it themselves, but of course that didn't last for the whole time but - you know, we had that when it came along. And - Sundays we never had any cooked breakfast at all, it was always cold ham and boiled eggs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was cold all the way through the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 All the day, there was no cooking done on a Sunday. That - that was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would you have for midday dinner during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, roast meat and whatever it was. Usually we - we always had a hot roast meat o
n - on - on Saturday - nine times out of ten beef was the thing then, it was the staple thing. That would be cold on Sunday, hashed up on Monday. Tuesdays you had perhaps a bit of mutton and that would last you until - the Friday or Saturday and then you'
d probably have a - stew or a mince pie or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd buy these out because you hadn't got refrigeration?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, you had to buy your meat you see. Except - except pig you see, everybody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How about chicken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, well there was plenty of poultry you see but I mean that came in between you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would it be your own poultry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Bread and cheese as a rule. Bread and cheese and pickle. You had a good meal midday
 you didn't want it in the evening you see. That's how it's changed now isn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was just before you went to bed anyway wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, but then that didn't matter. My grandfather lived until he was ninety-two or three and he'd sit dow
n at half past ten at night and eat a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 darned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
 great plateful of meat and pickles and he'd go straight to bed and sleep 'til the next morning. So - where's the harm coming on that you see. Oh well it's true. It's true. And drink three or four glasses of cider with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have drinks with your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Cider was the staple drink, yes. Kids had lemonade you know. Homemade lemonade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What meals would you have cider with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Midday. No, midday and supper. Those were the two meals you had cider.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You had tea for the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Tea, well yes, coffee wasn't like as popular as it is now at all. Tea was the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Very occasionally. We did have one - help in the house 
that was - keen on - baking bread. She was a Cornish person. But not - not - not really you know, you see it wasn't a recognized thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It wouldn't be your mother so much, it would be the help?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, because she was keen on it. I don't say 
my mother couldn't bake bread, but they didn't - she didn't do it, a lot of people did and still do it. There's a farmer across the other side of the bridge always her bread now and makes all her cakes the same way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But otherwise normally you'd buy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, get the bread - four pound loaves in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you get them from Totnes or Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Buckfastleigh baker would call. With a horse and trap twice a week. And the butcher would call you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you get your meat from Buckfastleigh or Totnes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh whichever you - you know, we always got a joint at Totnes on the Friday as I told you when they went to the market you see. And probably they'd get an odd joint at the middle of the week from - Buckfastleigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever brew any beer as well as cider?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How about vegetables or bottled fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, we used to grow all our vegetables and - and they used to bottle fruit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, all we'd got. Plums and - you know, the whole - the whole - the whole lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have an orchard up at Rill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh quite a lot in garden, a big walled garden - with apple trees and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did that sort of keep you all the year round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, and - and sold heaps. Sold heaps in addition to what we wanted you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Always mother made homemade jam, marmalade, the whole thing. And my wife still does.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How about pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Chutneys and all that, oh yes, just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever make wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No. No, my mother never touched wine at all. It wasn't as popular then as it is now, it's come very popular now hasn't it, wine making and beer brewing. Oh yes, well my wife makes her won. You know, she - always making wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say you were self-sufficient in vegetables and fruit, did you ever buy any at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
I doubt it. I never remember - that wee did. I suppose if you had a bad year and you were out of onions and the old French boys used to come }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 with them on the sticks - and s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
ell 'em so much a bunch you know, a string, at the door, they used to call you know. Oh yes, French onions. Oh yes, come across on a bicycle and - go right round. We had them here until - quite recently. French onions. And when they - when 
they get the tunnel we shall get 'em here every morning before breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You wouldn't have anything like tinned or dried vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, it was an unheard of thing. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When did they come in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - I - I - you see - there wa
s - there was an alteration after the first war wasn't there. Things began to come then but in the country districts it was very few, I mean, they were just not - and particularly amongst country people, I think people in towns used tines. But - we didn't
. We didn't at all. Because we were more or less self-supporting you see, that's just it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you ever get extra meat such as rabbit from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh not from poaching, but we'd get rabbits in our own right, you have as many as you like. And p
heasants you see. I mean, there they were, just for the - just for the going out and shooting them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You weren't sort of barred from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. Oh no, he used to allow his tenants you see and when they had a shoot you always had a brace of phea
sants passed in. All tenants had that privilege whenever they went out you'd get a brace of pheasant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time of year would the shoots be? A certain time of year would it be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, there's a closed season for pheasants you see. You can only
 shoot them now - they're out of season now from the first of February you see. And they come in again next October. And partridges come in on the first of September.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Is that a Royal Decree?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It's the Game Law. It's the Game Law.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was there much poaching went on round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, quite a lot. But - they very rarely got caught. But they knew it happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was it much of a trouble or was it just a pinprick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, it wasn't - it wasn't serious to that extent. I expect there was
 a lot of poaching done that nobody ever knew anything about. But as far as salmon are concerned - since 1930 - I knew where I could go and buy - a salmon at a shilling a pound any time I wanted one. Well they must have been poached mustn't they. But I di
d
n't know where I got 'em from, I mean, that - that didn't worry me. You see, 'cos I mean that's - that's long as that. And previous to that I mean you could go down - my grandfather's told me that when he was farming - he would go and cut a nut stick off 
f
rom a hedge going down to the river and get a bit of rip cord from the saddler and a nice big pin on the bottom with a worm and you'd go down and wait ten minutes, you could catch a salmon and take it and go home, there was no restrictions. It was open fo
r
 anybody to catch 'em. And the - and they weren't stealing the fish. Then you see as soon as they started - putting restrictions on - then everybody came fishing you see from far and wide, the motor car came and the people came from all over the place. Th
e
n you got the pollution going into the rivers. I think the tar'll wash off the road was the start of this, because let's face it, all the sewers of Buckfastleigh - and the effluent from the mills all went crude into the river Dart in those days. But it ha
dn't got any chemicals in it you see. But there were tons - loads of fish the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 re. I know this is not on the D}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
art, but - there you are, that's what we're facing aren't we. You see, anything that becomes restricted, everybody wants to get at. Isn't it, in everything. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There were public health acts in the 19th century weren't there to stop things like clogging up rivers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well you see, as far as the Dart's concerned it didn't clog up because it's a very fast flowing river. One night's rain on D
artmoor, down came about two feet of water and everything that was there went straight out to sea. It's - it's - i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
's the rivers that are - slower flowing that get - worst pollution you see, there's not so much trouble here. And you see it's tidal up to To
tnes Weir. And you've got a change of water there every twenty-four hours you see. No, it's not the bother that they've got up in the industrial No}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 th and all that where these - flatter parts of the country where the rivers just creep along, this thing dow
n here'll rise - it'll rise three feet in quarter of an hour. It's almost like a rain coming down and it's gone in another half an hour you see, it's all gone out to sea.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It's as quick as that is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, I've stood down by Austin's Bridge a
nd seen it, well you can stan there and see it rising when we used to get these floods, we don't get 'em now - as much and you gradually see it coming out onto the main road. And you go down in hour's time and it'll be gone back to - not quite normal but 
gone right back off the road you know,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of livestock would you keep on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh general - cattle and sheep and pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And chickens and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, yes. And - keep chickens and ducks you see. And nearly everybody
 had tame pigeons in those days, we had tame - tame pigeons because there was pigeon holes all around the buildings. Damn nuisance they were too, but that's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You didn't use them for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many men would you have on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Two and a boy. Yes, two - in addition to my father you see and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And this boy who lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Boy who lived in, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that sort of standard for farms round Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I would say so, yes. Yes. Yes. You see
 the farm was about two hundred, well - they used to reckon one man to fifty acres. So that's - roughly - give and take a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you reckon you'd eat meat just about every day of the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Pretty well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Just in the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father ever have any more than the rest of you, being a working man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well it - it was pretty common to have two platefuls. For - him and any of the children that wanted it. Two helpings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. As long as you didn't make too much noise, you know, choked off occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh you - well we were encouraged to eat all vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Why was that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well because they were considered to be good for you. All vegetables as they came in season were always cooked and you were expe
cted to have some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would happen if you left some food uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - I mean it'd be - you'd be choked off, you know what I mean. And the old saying u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 sed to be to put it crudely, bel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ly'll find brains. And there you are. You've got to eat it haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You were all right to ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. And put them in a certain way on the plate when you'd finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who taught you that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh, mother and father, that was the way they were brought up and they way we were brought up. You weren't allowed to sit with your elbows on the table and - and - and - and fork in one hand and - and knife in the other up in the air like this, when y
ou were not using them they had to be put on the plate - properly. And when you'd finished - they had to be put on the plate - properly. No - leaving them anywhere, they put on properly and taken off.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Could you bring a toy or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I don't - I don't know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When could you leave the table, do you remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
You could ask to be - if you could get down from the table when you'd finished eating. And if you'd behaved and eaten your grub you could go but if you'd l
eft some you were told you'd got to sit there until you eat it. And sometimes you got left after everybody was gone, but somebody -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever have any sort of upsets over this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh we had those things, of course you did with younger children I
 mean, you do don't you. But you see when you being to get eight or nine you're glad to eat. When you're growing and you're out in the fresh air all day you see you get hungry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you were at school you wouldn't have the midday meal during the week would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Quite. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would you do when you weren't eating in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh well, then you'd have a good meal when you got home. You see, a - what they used to call a high tea. With whatever there was going and - probably an apple tart or something to follow up. Something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would that high tea consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well meat as a rule. Meat as a rule of some sort. Either hot or cold. Could be hot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say you had tea in the middle of the afternoon, late afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would that be the same then as it would be when you came home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No. No, no. That was extra you see. And of course there was a custom then if - if father was late for his midday meal it was put into the oven and 
kept even hot until four 'clock that he could have a hot meal. It was put in the oven and covered up and he would eat it - when he came home, perhaps back from - the market, Totnes he'd been, you see, he may not get back 'til five o'clock, well he - then 
he'd have hi hot meal when he got back. Thing I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185  hated, I don't like heat - hott}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
ed up things at all. No. But there you are, that was it. That was it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would cook all the food, would your mother and this assistant cook it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would the cleaning woman have anything to do with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 She wouldn't do much to the cooking no, because she'd go again you see - she'd have her midday meal and clear up and then she'd be gone.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What times did she do? I think I asked that didn't I?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, she used to come in the morning at eight o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 More or less. Yes, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was it a hard and fast rule or just sort of convenient?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, father sat at the head of the table and - mother on his right and - kids were opposite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How would breakfast be served?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well you see to begin with it had to be cooked on an open fire. And there was no way of keeping it hot, so my mother or - the help - would be cooking an
d it would be put on a plate and put straight across on the table, as it came out of the pan or whatever you were cooking you see. An open hearth fire was used. You see, the range wouldn't be - up to that heat by that time of the day, the range was lighte
d after that and that would be used for the midday meal. But breakfast was cooked on an open fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time would your father be up before that to work on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh he'd get somewhere about six to half past and he'd come in to breakfast at about eight. That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would he have anything before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Cup of tea. Before he started, yes. And that had to be - that had to be boiled over an open fire. Didn't go over and flip down the catch you know on the electric. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd have breakfast and then as a boy you'd go off to school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you were at home, not with your auntie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, that's right. Go down and catch the train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you'd have breakfast before you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Take your sandwiches, and your - lesson bag with the books in. And that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have to buy your own school books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They were provided by the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I took it they were, yes. I don't remember. I think you had to pay something extra towards books. But I wouldn't know you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was all taken in account with the fees?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. With the fees, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 If there was anything on the table you wanted like the salt could you ask someone to pass it or did you have to wait until it was offered 
to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh no, oh no, no, no, oh no. It was passed around to you and - you probably had to say, I'd like some salt, if they didn't push it across but - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did your younger brother and sister sit before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In a baby's chair. You know, these little things, pull up and down, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they feed themselves or would they be fed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh they had to be fed for a time naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would do that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh mother principally. They used to look 
after kids then you know. If they were doing the kids the kid - the help was doing the - more or less getting the meal organized and passing round you know this sort of business you see. And of course one thing I forgot to say that before any meal - my fa
ther said grace. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Every single meal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. Yes? Always. You sit down - grace, he'd say, and he'd say grace. That was it. It was done generally, around you know, when you went to - a few places went and we kids used to remark, they don't say grace there mummy, why do we say it here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And what did she say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, she said, because it's the right thing to do. You see, well that's it. That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you find your mother was an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 My mother was very easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Yes. A very united family, and my mother was a - was a very - sort of - what can I say - considerate and a loveable type of person. I mean - we thought no end of our mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So if you had any worries you could always go to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well my father you see was a man and he - was rather more - severe and to the point. When he said something you knew you had to do it pretty quick. Even when you were go
ing to school or after you left school. I've seen him at the breakfast table - when everything's finished and - this is after mind - this is - yes, prior to 1918 I suppose, and I've seen him take his watch out of his pocket and - have a look and said, do 
y
ou realize it's ten minutes past eight, are you people going to do any work today or not? And up he'd get and walk out. And well of course you soon had to go after him you see and that was it you see. That was the type of man he was, he expected people to
 be with him when it was time to move.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother fit in with this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well yes, but of course she used to favour us kids a bit you see and - all right, he's gone now - you'd better finish. You see. But - but that's it, that - that's family life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh we had to respect them. You see, they always expected to be addresse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 
d as mother and father. Not by C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 hristian names as they do today. And we had to respect other people. If you saw the
 padre of the parish you would raise your hat to him. And if you met the landlord he was sir. Other people were just misters. And the - the - the men that worked for us was called by}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185  their C}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 hristian names.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How old were the other two then, not the young boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I told you, they - they - they came to us before they were married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 All of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
The two brothers, they were two brothers you see, they came to us - one - on - unfortunately - yes, one unfortunately died when - when he was about fo
rty I think, something like that, but the other one was with the family all his life. And his son's been with the family all his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - you see - the idea was the
n that - I was going to be a farmer. And they naturally hoped that I should - find a partner probably from a farming community. Which was - my mother wasn't a - actually from a farm although her people were farmers but she wasn't from a farm but - that wa
s the general run you see and my wife as you - you know and see now, she - her father was a farmer, just the same you see. And when you marry a wife you see that's been a farmer and seen the - thing from the commencemen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185  of her life she knows the difficulties and she can help and be - sympathe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
ic towards things when they don't go right, whereas you get these - with all due respect to them, these girls that come out from the town and it's a novelty. Oh yes, I've been to live out on a farm, it's going to be wo
nderful, you see. Yes, but - the novelty wears off after three or four years you know. I mean I've seen it all through my life. Some of them are excellent. But - you do see a lot that - fall by the wayside I'm afraid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you think your parents sort of brought this fact over to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh no, they didn't do that. They didn't influence me in any way. You see, there's rather an extraordinary thing because - I'm afraid I had plenty of girlfriends as I was growing, all over the place, and then you see I 
went in the services and I saw quite a different - had quite a different outlook on life with a - meeting all you did and going where I did, and yet I came back - and in 1928 married a - farmer's daughter which - I didn't know when I went away in 19 - 17.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about the girls before, what kind were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh all and sundry. I mean - girls you met at school you know how it goes along you see.. Oh yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would you meet them at school, you were at a boys school weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well 
yes, but then you see we used to have dances in the villages in the evenings you know, I mean - there was more - there was more social life in the small villages then than there is at the present time because they'd got nowhere else to go. You see, if the
y
 wanted to go to Totnes, well there was no bus you know. There was a train but - the last one wasn't very late and look where you'd to walk from there to get to where you live you see. And there were - there were - there were village dances and - one afte
r
 the other and one village helped the other and they - they went around in a - in - in a sort of circle you see. But there was more village life altogether than there is today, and - and Christmas parties and all this you see for various people, it was qu
i
te different. Now you see we've got a new village hall here right opposite which we built in '52, well for twelve months it went, now - hardly anybody wants it. All our rising generation here go off on a - in their cars or on their motor bikes. You don't 
see 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you think in those days all the little villages would all have their own little community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And Staverton, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would you go, would you go to Buckfastleigh or more towards Staverton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 We'd go to Buckfastleigh. B
ut you see - remember we went to Staverton in 1916. You see, it was then on from when I got - into that circle I mean to say of going out evenings and that. Previous to that there wasn't much up to sixteen you see. You didn't go out much then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was mainly after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes, these things happened, which is - longer than you intend going on this isn't it really, yes. Well up to that time that we left - we left - up to 1916 - things like that were very restricted. It was principally private parties - that we went to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 To do with your parents more then you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember what would happen on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Nothing extraordinary, no, you'd have a birthday cake for whoever it was but there was no - no big celebration at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have birthday cards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. But not like you get 'em today. Not a bit, not. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have special festivities at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well you see - a thumping great meal of - more than you should really eat
, which you felt ill for a day or two after, but then that was the part of enjoying Christmas. And then you'd have games - organized games in the house. Cards and games, the older people would play cards, some would play whist and - some would play nap, n
a
p was very popular round here in those days, and - and - the kids had to amuse themselves, you see - as a rule one room was set aside as a playroom when you had a big - house as we had and that's where we had our games for the children, in there. I rememb
er when we had our first gramophone with a horn to the thing which was a wonderful - thing. Prior to that the help used to play the piano for - you know, games, kiss in the ring and all this goes on you see. And that was it, postman's knock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you'd have a lot of people coming at Christmastime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, I told you, it would - it would last - yes, you'd go from one to the other you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have a regular sort of thing where you'd stay in on Christmas day and have people come to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Nobody - you did nothing much on Christmas Day. We spent the - Christmas Day as a family, these things used to start on Boxing Day. And up to the time they were there we went to our - my grandfather and grandmother's house - Christmas Day. And her sons an
d daughters brought their family with 'em and it was quite a party, we used to sit down about twenty-five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it wouldn't be in your place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That's be at my grandfather's place you see, but then they'd all be asked back to us. But they may not al
l come together, but I mean we thought nothing of sitting down to twelve or fourteen to a meal. Midday meal - principally, not in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about the farm hands and the assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, they would be working I mean - they - well, the 
help in the house would be in it. I mean, she'd help to do the work, but the men outside they - they - they were nothing to do with that side of it at all you see, because they would be working you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They wouldn't work on Christmas Day or Boxing Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. Well they made their own - they made their own -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about the boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh well I expect he went home. You see. He'd go home for Christmas in any case. Probably Boxing Day. I can't quite remember you know, not the detail like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have musical instruments, you say you played the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Only a piano, but then of course some had musical instruments, but - they were few and far between. You were looked upon as a bit of cissy if you thought about wanting to learn the
 way to play a violin. Oh yes, yes, you were, oh yes, yes. I always wanted to learn to play the piano, I was never allowed to. No, not allowed to. My sister, pounds were spent on her and she never played the damn thing after she left school. But I'd have 
loved to have been able to play a piano, specially when I was in the services because it was just - just what everyone was looking for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But you had a piano in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who played that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 My mother used to play it, and most of the helps we had could play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But they didn't teach you to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, they didn't - said they weren't going to waste money on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They didn't just teach you casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. I just helped to five finger exercise, God Save the King or something like that. No. We never had no opportunity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you think it was more Christmas week rather than anything on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - you see - there again -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have any guests or friends round on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, in - in t
his respect you see. My mother's birthday was in June, and my sister's birthday was in July. And - at the beginning of June we were usually in the midst of hay harvest. And we used to cut some revels down by this river, and we would invite quite a lot of 
-
 friends, perhaps twenty to twenty-five, to come in the afternoon and have a picnic in the hayfield. You see. Well that happened to come right for June. For my mother. Well my sister's birthday was twelve month - a - a month later, but we still probably h
a
d a bit of hay around if you had a late harvest. And some times you'd be getting into corn you see, but that consisted of a picnic. And then of course - farmers all around in the area used to go off - for a day's holiday with their ponies and traps and go
 to Dartmoor. Drive right out on the moor and take everything they wanted to eat and drink, and go out there and - and that was it, that was a day's outing for the children you see. Probably that was on somebody's birthday you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you did the rounds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. But very - very limited, I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In the summer when the weather was nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes, and I mean you could say twelve mile radius roughly. Gru wouldn't go much further than that you see, twelve miles there and twelve miles back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You said you sang hymns on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would that be in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So they'd play the piano for that would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 My mother or - or - I say the help. My mother principally, that was - what she used to do. And my father join
ed in. Oh yes, we were all in on this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did he ever play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Like me, he wasn't allowed to learn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was this sort of normal practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well it - it seemed to be - oh yes. I can't think of any farmer's son - who in the - ah - ra
dius of fens that he can play the piano. And very few girls learnt. Very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And yet you had the piano there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Everybody had a piano. Lot of people had grand pianos. Oh yes. Oh yes. Oh it was done to have an upright piano. No, it was part of the
 house - that was it. My sister's still got ours I think where she lives now. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would your parents play games with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They wouldn't separate, they'd play their own games you play yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, no. Well, they may - they may sometimes, but they - they would - they'd muck in. They'd play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would they play with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I tell you - card games principally they'd join in, they woul}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 
dn't join in with ring-a-ring-a-r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 osie and all that sort of thing but - but they'd be around you know. Oh yes, they'd be around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they play hide and seek and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, oh yes, there was more in the summer you see when you went out, but of course you'd get in the house, you could do it in a big ho
use like we had because there was lots of places you could there hide there and they'd never find you. But that was principally out in the garden, we had a big garden. Well you've seen Rill garden. You know how big it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd ride the horses and things like that as kids?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have to go for riding lessons or anything to begin with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, we were self taught I'm afraid. And - that came in fairly well - perhaps I was lucky but we found in the services, I was in the
 REME depot down at - Woolwich for - eighteen months training these - boys to ride. And - we found the people that could - we could get to ride military style the easiest were those that had never seen a horse before. You see, a lot that you get that thin
k they know the way to ride but - I was fortunate I suppose but - 'cos I was in the - one of the instructors down at Woolwich in the grand depot for nearly twelve months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose that's what attracted you in the first place, the fact that you could work with the horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
I didn't want - didn't fancy this foot slogging at all. I said, if I've got to go I'm going to get up and get on before I'm old enough and I'll volunteer and go in a horse regiment, and I got in the horst artillery and there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Heaps of books. Some of them there now that we had, kids books. You know the usual }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185  children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
s stories, gradually going up and up and up you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your parents read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, read to us a lot. Until we could read ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they read to themselves, would they have their own book collection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not a lot. My father did - later on in life but - they'd read the daily newspapers you see, or - and - and - books - magazines i
n connection with agriculture but not - as - not reading as you look upon reading today. They didn't do much of that. Well my parents didn't at any rate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember a funeral in the family at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, I can remember my grandfather and grandmother's funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When was that, was that after this period or before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 After. Yes, later than this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember a funeral in the family before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. I'm just trying to think, my aunt, that was after we went to Newtake in 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did your parents expect you to behave towards your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh well - the same as they say to you now. Up to a certain age boys think girls are a damned nuisance and when they get a bit older they think they're very use
ful, I mean the same thing applied then. Oh we're not going to play with the girls, we used to say, you know, and the girls wouldn't play with the boys, you know. Just - nothing heated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did your parents think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I never heard my f
ather swear once in his life. He'd say damn, but nothing else. He was very - strict about that, very strict. And we naturally were, but I'm afraid when I got in the services I thought what sort of world I'd come into. But there you are. And that - that wa
s it you see. That - that - no, they were very strict about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well that depended you see on what the conversation was about you see. If they were talking business naturally you would - 
you'd be told to go out in the other room and amuse yourself, if they wanted to talk about something like that, and you went and you didn't hesitate about it at all if you were sent - you go out there for - we have got some - I want to talk to so and so a
b
out something or other which is nothing to do with you, well then you went out. Then you - naturally when they'd finished they'd open the door and say you can come back again if you want to now, or probably you were doing something else and didn't want to
 go back again. Only just - commonsense I mean, there was no hard and fast rule about anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you were at school did you ever have things like parents evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No. No. Used to have the annual prize giving, which parents were invited to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you go along as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Oh - they probably both would go you see and then they had a tea party after you know. Yes, they had that. But that was all. And of course parents were invited to the school sports every year. 
Down on the playing field down there at - Totnes. They could go to that you see and they could go to cricket matches. Football matches if they wanted to. But very few did from a distance because you see they hadn't got any way of getting there. It was qui
te a job, I mean you had to arrange that the horse was available and the trap was available and somebody to drive it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And being on a farm it's not easy to give up the work is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well that's it you see, we hadn't got the opportunity to do
 those things, but there was the opportunity for the town people - in particular to attend, and they did. They did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well you'd get a good ticking off I suppose like you do 
now, I don't know, I don't remember, I - I can't remember any - any - any very serious thing that did happen. No doubt there were heaps of them but I just can't remember one now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh both. Both. Definitely. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about Saturdays, did anything special happen on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, just work, that's all. Just the same as any other day. Of course there were football matches which you - local 
matches you see among the villages which - if you were interested you could go to, but - you had to do your work before you went and - in the wintertime feeding cattle, horses and all this and you had to do it when you got back. But - they went, I mean do
n
't think they didn't go because I had a bicycle when I was about fourteen years old. And that was a way and means of getting around about you see. Oh yes, and then if you - you had a pony to ride you could ride a pony into Buckfastleigh, stick it in one o
f the stables and then all the pubs had stables in those days, and go to your football match and then ride back.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about when you were at school, would you work on the farm on Saturdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I used to help, yes, afternoons. Yes. There again you s
ee my brother had the advantage, he was in the football team and everything because he - he - that was it you see. The older one had to be home - mind I had some time off, don't get me wrong on this but - you were expected to do quite a bit when there was
 
a busy thing going on on the farm you see. And - funnily enough you used to like doing it. You were annoyed if when you got home and found something had been done that you expected you were going to be there in time to help about. You know, I can't go int
o details but that - that was just the outlook on life you see. You were so interested in it that you wanted to be there to see it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Everything would stop on the farm on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, except the essentials, yes, cows you see and the feeding in the
 winter. That's all. Nothing else was done on the Sunday at all. Not with us. I - I mean there were exceptions to that. But - people respected Sunday more then than they do now. You see, you wouldn't - you wouldn't - you'd try and not arrange to have a fi
e
ld of hay to carry on a weekend, 'cos the weather would beat you every time but even so and the same with the corn but you see now they go out and start a job on a Sunday morning now, it doesn't matter does it. It's just gone all - kind of opposite, all h
aywire you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 All the roads and things like that seem to be being done on Sunday and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was much more observed in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. I wouldn't know about the towns you see. But I do know that ours c
hurches here, we've got two in this parish and they were reasonably full every Sunday. You see, well now if you get half a dozen people there that's it. You see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many churches are there in Buckfastleigh, there's two Church of England are there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
In Buckfastleigh, yes. Yes, and two here in this parish you see. Got this one up here and the one down in - down Staverton village, down the river. Of course that's a very old church down there. St Paul de Yong that is. Very old church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would the whole family go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Oh yes. And used - we used to walk when the weather was decent. Or you had -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Which one did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Buckfastleigh, right up on top of the hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many times a day would you go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Once
. We weren't expected to go afternoons nor evenings. Until we got when we wanted to go out evenings then we made an excuse to go to church again. You see, as all young people do. And that was it you see. And if you said you were going to church that was q
uite all right. But you don't be too late back mind. All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You weren't in the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Never went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 None of you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No, nobody at all ever went to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever have anything to do with the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any outings you'd go on with the church, they'd all be got up by the Sunday school would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There was a church outing but I never remember going on it. And there was a Sunday school outing but I 
say I never remember going on it. Never remember going on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Both your parents were Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And the whole family went once on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any other social activities organized by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
My mother used to go to - I suppose do the - do the church run the mother's unions? I believe they do don't they, she used to go to that, she was a member of that. And of course they used to have little social events in Buckfastleig
h, they had whist drives in aid of something or other and - sale of work for the church and then - she used to take part in that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often were they then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well perhaps once - no, less than that, maybe once a fortnight or once a month you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember whether the church ran any temperance club in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, every night when we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would teach you to say them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, we were
 told - I mean - mother principally taught us our prayers naturally but - as we became older it just became a habit and we always did it. Always did it you see, we - we looked upon it as the right thing to do before you get in bed. I don't know whether th
e
y do now I'm sure. Not a lot is there. I - I know - I don't know see what the - what they - I - now remember when I went in the services I felt an awful nay, and I just couldn't get myself to do this you know in the first barrack road I was in, but after 
a
bout a week I did and a lot did after that you know. And as you became nearer to when you were going across the water where things were happening you thought more about those sort of things then you see and it became to you to do this. And naturally we ha
d a padre and he impressed on us - that this was - a decent and sensible thing to do and - and we did it. There were a few rebels of course but then you get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you in charge of men when you went overseas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, yes, I was on the signals a
s a sergeant on the - on the signals side of the thing. I used to look after the range finder for the Major on the battery, it was all connected with the - with the - signals it was you see, that side of it. Where you he your own horse to ride and carried
 all your equipment you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember if your father took any interest in politics when you were still a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not as it would matter. They had the usual - neighbourly arguments. But you see then it was Liberals and Conservatives, and I've 
got an idea my grandfather was a Liberal. And my father tended that way where they felt that the middle classes were the ones that should - govern the country. Somebody to look after the top dogs and somebody to help up the lower ones a bit. And the middl
e classes should be, I - I - that's what I -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they be Liberals or Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The middle classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Liberals. Oh yes, Buckfastleigh was a very strong Liberal place in those days, and the Mills were still there and they were
 Liberal absolutely to the man. But that didn't influence him you see because he came from just outside Totnes. And Totnes was absolutely the other way around, they were all blue in there you see. But Buckfastleigh being a little mill town was always look
ed upon as a stronghold for Liberalism. And that's where my grandfather was brought}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
up, in Buckfastleigh. O outside Buckfastleigh. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was this your father's father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. YES. Yes. My father's father, and I always had an idea that he was a Libe
ral. But you see people didn't tell you what they were in those days. No quite, it was quite different you see. Quite different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say the Liberals were the middle classes, what were the Conservatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I think nearly all farmers were Conser
vatives. And I'm not going to tell you - now - my father was not but I think he had Liberal tendencies and I think it came from - the way he was brought up you see with his - with his father who was undoubtedly a Liberal. Undoubtedly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother have any views on politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. She didn't take any interest in that sort of thing at all. No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember your father voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, the trap and - and they used to drive and take pe
ople to polls just like they do with motor cars now. Oh yes, they'd take the men if they wanted to go for one and they'd take neighbours if they hadn't got any form of transport and they'd make up a good old trap load you see and take the whole lot. Oh ye
s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You don't really have an idea what party your father would have voted for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not definitely, no, no, no, I couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their emp
loyers, do you know if you father felt himself under that kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No I don't think that is so. Not the experience I've had, with our men or with my father and the landlord, no. Definitely no. None at all, not so far as we were concerned anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was he a member of any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not that I am aware of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He didn't work for any of the parties at elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your parents take part in any political activity at all except at general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time, apart from Christmastime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well you see in the summer gardening. And in the winter as I told you sitting round the fire playing cards or something like that. There w
asn't nothing much else to do. But they used to work long hours you see my father used to go out every night and go - with the - with the boy that was in the house and go around the yard and see all the cattle were all right in fact and feed some of them.
 They had a pretty busy life and used to go to bed at ten o'clock you know because things were moving at six in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would your mother be up for that time as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well not quite, but then she - he'd expect to come in at - just after h
alf past seven and breakfast all ready on the table. Somebody had to do it. You know, it have to be done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So there wouldn't have been an awful lot of spare time anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would Saturday routine be, when would he finish on Saturday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well that didn't matter. Saturday was another day of the week, that's all. And you must remember he went to - a cattle market once a fortnight which took the whole of a Tuesday. And he went to Totnes practically every Friday afternoon. Which 
was another half day, leaving home about one and arriving back about five. After driving the seven miles each way. But then he had to do his work, when he got back you see, well he had no - you see - but then it was organised in that way you see. They kne
w
 that was going to happen. And they organized the other work in with that you see, harvest time perhaps if he couldn't go, well - they had to get to Totness some other way, somebody must go down and catch the train, there were plenty of trains in those da
ys you see from Buckfastleigh to Totnes. Plenty of trains.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of farm was Rill Farm, was it more livestock than crops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh general mixed. Mixed. General farm. Certain amount of corn you see and cattle food and - and certain amount of hay ma
de and grazing sheep you see, it was general mixed farm with a few pigs. Which - this part of South Devon in those days con - consisted of. I mean this specialization of various things has only come in quite recently hasn't it. You see, when I started in 
-
 in '28, it was similar thing. You had a bit of everything. And you were told that - you mustn't put all your eggs in one basket. But I always thought that you wanted to specialize in one or two things but - I - I wasn't brought up that way you see. And t
hat's it. Well of course the pattern of farming is changing - very much, specially this last ten year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 In those days it was more sort of hard graft and less equipment to help you, less technology to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No machines at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have the vet round very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Not as often as they do now because farmers were - especially some - stock farmers were - not as clever as a vet, don't get me wrong, but they had remedies that they used to use. You see, local remedies. And you see there was a man - they weren't vet}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
inary's, they were not qualified, they were called farriers, and they used to go around and do all the odd jobs of - if you had difficulty with a cow calving and - if you wanted calves castrated and all that these - these -
 these - these fellows went round and did that, they went around on a horse and called into the farms you see and they were called farriers. They had a certain amount of knowledge - of - of a vet}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 inary, but they were not qualified you see, they hadn't been to college and got their letters or anything like that at all. You see, the vet}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
inary came in after the first war, in the middle of - along about 1925 to '30 they became much more prominent around here then. You see, T.T. came in and all sorts of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was your father insured for any sort of problems like fowl pest or whatever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No, you couldn't insure for - for - for - for foot and mouth, my grandfather had foot and mouth disease I've heard him say in somewhere about 1903 and '04 and he cured every one of 'em. You see, they had a very - I think it was stock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 land car they used to plaster on their feet. And you see there was no -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That worked did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Well they know it does now. But you see the thing is it would spread all ove
r the country, that - that's the snag today because of the transport. You see, it can be carried on the - on - on the tyres of a motor car, it can come in your yard and it may not be long but it'll take it out, the next farm it goes in they get it in thre
e
 or four days. Even with the cattle. Oh yes, you can cure fot and mouth quite easily, but you see it's - it's - it's trouble that the infection would cause throughout the country and - with all the cattle and all the set-up there is today it would be just
 impossible to deal with it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was your father or mother a member of any savings club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not that I know of, there wasn't such thing in those days I reckon was there, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No sick clubs or funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I don't remember any of it, not in the country districts at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they have a boot club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You said your father used to take you to the races, did he bet when he went to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I wouldn't know you see up to that age, you must remember sixteen you forget some}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
things. I know - we used to be taken up to Buckfastleigh in a pony and trap and - the races were held and we were picked up and taken home again you see. I mean there wasn't a motor car on the co
urse. That was only - four in hands and all these from all over the place you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were these races crowded out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. Not the extent they are today 'cos you see - literally hundreds of people walked there from Buckfastleigh and they came by tr
ain, they ran special trains from Totnes to Buckfastleigh for races. Race - go from Totnes to Buckfastleigh for about a bob return. Race special. And they were full these times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was one of the major events of the sporting year I suppose?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It was there, Buckfastleigh, yes. Yes. Then they lost it altogether you see, it's gone now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your father attend any clubs or pubs in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He used to - quite often go to - into Buckfastleigh on a Saturday evening, and - I think he used to
 go to the club - they had a club, and played billiards. In addition to going and having a drink. You see, there was a billiard table at the Town Hall, and I - I - if I remember rightly they had - whether they could drink there or whether they had to just
 go down the yard, I'm not sure about that but - several farmers used to meet there on Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Mainly on Saturday night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, yes, he'd go Saturday nights as a rule. And then you see you'll pass the cottages where your men were, and they 
often wanted to go into the village on Saturday night for the same purpose and they would be given a lift, and - or back, if they saw them on the way or coming back you see. They helped each other over these difficulties you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother ever go along with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No, never. Not to my knowledge. You see, it was the woman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 \rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 s job then to look after the house and look after the children. That was her job and that's it. 'Course there were exceptions you know to these cases, you mustn'
t take this as being - the same with everybody. This is my experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother have any interests outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Only with relatives. No to there that I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How many relatives would you have living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, you
 see my father came from a family of nine. And they all lived to a pretty good age. You see, and they had children so that you might say there was quite a - quite a circle of - relatives. And then my father - my grandfather had a brother in Plymouth. Who 
had - quite a family, and you see that was within striking distance in those days with a train, it was easy to get to Plymouth. Trains from Totnes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about your mother's side, would there be a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, you see these people at Totne
s I told you where we used to stay when we went to school and - her relatives ran this kindergarten school and girls school. Well they were connected in Totnes - in a - you know, in a number of ways. Then she had a brother went to London who was a wholesa
l
e lace merchant with offices in Oxford Circus Avenue, he used to come down every - he was looked upon as the rich part of the family you see. And then she had a - she had another brother - sister that married another man in London that was in business. Th
ose cousins all came down to us to stay in the summer you see. To come down on the farm, it was the thing to do you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You had a constant flow of people in the summer then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. There was eight or ten of 'em you see, from the London - two f
amilies that came - down for their summer holidays and they'd stay with us perhaps six weeks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There were these spare rooms for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, plenty of room. Yes, quite, there was plenty of room for them of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So in the winter it'd be a bit quieter but in the summer there were lots of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That's right. Heaps of visitors in - the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd visit relatives more than neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. My father was very friendly with a bachelor neighbour who lived two farms away
, and in the winter he used to jump upon his horse after - perhaps eight o'clock, ride up to where we lived, stick his horse in the stable and go in and they'd play draughts until midnight, then he'd get up and ride home again. And that was an evening's e
n
tertainment. You see? That's what they did. You see, and - they'd talk about this you know, with their other friends, oh I did this - how's so and so, and - is that right is it, you see, and that's how they amused themself. Then they'd go playing nap just
 the same. And if they won five bob then they'd done something you know. That's nearly five quid today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That sort of betting wasn't disapproved of at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Oh no, no. They played ha'penny nap, farthing nap in some cases. Yes. And you wouldn't lose a lot you know or make a lot in a night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How did you get on with your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh very well. Reasonably well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you find you were closer to your brother than your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, I was closer to my sister because you see
 we were more the same age. He came along six years after you see and - as I tell you went - went of to public school, but my sister and I were always home you see, right up to when I got married. My sister and I were more - as one than he was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would you play with when you were young, would it be your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Or the neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well that was mixed I mean you see, that was mixed. You'd get neighbours children naturally. But we were pretty thick, my sis
ter and I you know, we did most things together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It's not as if you'd got many neighbours round there in close proximity is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, but you must remember down at Coleston, the next little farm on the way down there there were nine children down 
there. So we had plenty to play with in that respect. And they're all around now - or most of them. Yes. They're scattered around here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They had big families in those days didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Whereabout would you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh i
n the garden, round the fields, anywhere - wherever any work was going in you'd generally find your way around you know, whatever was happening you see. You'd get round and see what they were doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you play ball games and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Oh cricket and - football. Rounders. That was a very favourite game - with the kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever get in the way of the men working at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well now you see the men used to encourage us to come with them and to - to learn the way to do w
hat they were doing. You see that was it, that was part of our life you see. I mean I learnt things to do then which I shouldn't have learnt properly any other way, I mean - when I was about twelve years old I could take three horses and a double furrow p
l
ough and go and plough a field if I wanted to, because I'd been with a man from when I - you see, they encouraged you to come along with them. It's the same with cutting and laying a hedge, well you went out with the man that was doing it and you learnt t
he way to do it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So a lot of your games would be educational in the sense of learning your trade?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Oh yes. YES. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Good God yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose on the farm there was lots of dirt to roll around in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you ever discouraged from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever belong to any youth organizations at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No, no, no. There weren't any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about the Y.M.C.A. and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, we never joined that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were they there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, there was a Y.M.C.A. in Buckfastleigh. Yes. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That was the Hamblyn thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They built it. Built the place and gave it to 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that normal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well I - I wouldn't think so. Wouldn't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So they were quite big philanthropists then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well quite, and you see they had - they employed nearly all the people in Buckfastleigh in the mills you see, and they looked after them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But you wouldn't have much to do with the Hamblyns really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have any hobbies when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I used to be very keen on collecting -
 various leaves and flowers and pressing them in a book. I remember I had a big book of all the wild flowers I could lay my hands on, and - variegated leaves, that was one thing. Anything connected with nature you see. As I - I know I keep repeating mysel
f
 but that was our life you see, we hadn't go anything else to do. You just had to amuse yourself on it, then you see others collected butterflies. Others collected birds eggs which there were thousands of then you see, now it's - it's quite different you 
see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You had fishing as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, we had fishing you see and - and I had a gun when I was old enough to carry one. Used to go out shooting. Rabbits and all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd go for walks an awful lot wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you had a bicycle when you were fourteen years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 About fourteen, fifteen, yes. I remember I had a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever go to anything like theatres?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I told you we - we used to go once to the pantomime. Once a year at Christmas time. Not - not - not any other time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Nothing like music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would there be any sort of village concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There was in Buckfastleigh but we - you see, you've got to remember we left when we were sixteen you see, we hadn't got to 
that age really. You see, it was rather different, we used to go to Totnes - from 1922 up to - up to - up - up to - up to the when we got married you see, where they did have - entertainment in various forms, travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ing - trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
ling shows and all this sort of things you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You can't remember much before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, well - we didn't have the opportunity you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Nothing like fairs, trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ling fairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They used to come once a year to Buckfastleigh, we were taken there as kids, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What were they like, were they like modern fairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes, except that it was all driven by steam engines. And - they hadn't got the wonderful things they've got today, you know, there was always the old - round-abouts with the horses and all thi
s business, and - and what was the other thing the - we used to be so keen on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often would they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Once a year, there was Buckfastleigh f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ir week, there was Totnes fair week, Newton fair week, they still do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time of year was it in Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh well, various times. I think Buckfastleigh was in October. Newton is in September you see. Well then you see the - the fairs all come now for the regattas. And they used to then in those days, just the same, they'd come two or three times a year.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they make ka big show of harvest festival in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well more than they do today because more people went to church. But the service was similar to what it is today, they decorated the church and - we took corn and apples and stuff you see to decorate, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would anything special happen on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever have anything like pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well no, you see, you don't want pets on farms do you you see. No, not - because you've got pr
actically every animal to deal with as it comes along you see and - you know, that type of animal. No, we didn't have pets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say you played football and cricket through the school quite a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever play rugby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever get any pocket money from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Yes. Not a lot but - I forget you see up to sixteen years of age how much I got but - we weren't allowed to have money and lib in any shape or form. If you were given a shilling y
ou had something. You see. And - I can remember when - pound note, you thought you were made when you had a pound note given to you you see, it was a lot of money. When you realize that farm workers were only getting thirty-three and sixpence a week. For 
wages. You had a pound note you were getting on you know. And you see before that time farm workers worked for thirteen shillings a week. I've heard my grandfather say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They went on strike in 1874?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They wanted a twelve hour day or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Well he remembered that my grandfather you see, I've heard him talk about it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would most of your friends at this time be from other farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Oh, by going to Totnes, mixed you see. Some would be town a
nd some would be country, but there were several farmers - other farms - from farms in the district to myself, but we also got friendly - with townspeople which I say I think did a terrific lot of good by going in there you see, we got mixed up with quite
 a different section altogether which did a lot of good I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you kept these friends all your life really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Oh yes, I see 'em now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they ever come back to the farm at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not weekends but they used to come for these
 - these - picnics in the summer, the - hayfield picnics, you could ask who you liked, it didn't matter, you could ask 'em, as long as they could get there, that was the main thing. You see, of getting from A to B. But - it's quite different than it was.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things would you spend your pocket money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Sweets principally. That was the main thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have a tuck shop or anything like that at the school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well there was one right outside. An old woman called Ryans and we 
used to go there and have a pennyworth of this and pennyworth of that and they would last you all the week. What you get for a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The teachers didn't mind you using the tuck shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. No. And we also used to get a - a boy come up with a b
asket at the lunch break at eleven o'clock with - three corner tarts and - and - and the round ones which you could buy and I think - you had two had for a ha'penny, something like that, I know they were t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 rribly cheap. He used to come up from the local bakery with 'em, in - in the yard when you had your break.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have regular pocket money every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes I think we must have you see, but I forget exactly what the amount was but I think we must have because we get a - but then you got s
ometimes you hadn't got any money to buy one and you'd ask somebody to buy one for you and you'd say you'd get one for them next time, you know how boys are, you - you generally get one somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family, you say the cleaning woman came in once a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would any relations ever come in to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Any friends pop in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, not to mention, not - not worth mentioning, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would happen if your mother was ill or confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, we just had to get somebody to - you know, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would the assistant and the cleaning woman take over?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. They were capable of taking over because you see they actual
ly were as one of the family. They lived with you you see. But that was - always arranged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember anything like your younger brother or sister being born, what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Can't remember any of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were they born in Rill Farm or a nursing home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh I think in the farm. I think all three of us were. Can't remember about myself but I think - I can't remember me sister but I - could remember when my brother arrived because I was six you see. And he definitely was born in - in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would happen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well they had a nurse you see for a week. They used to go round then these nurses you see. Doctor would come and - do the job and then he'd leave a nurse you see and - you'd have a nurse for a week, live
 with you in the house as one of the family you see. Just to get things going. That was usual you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That was mainly to look after your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have to pay for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There wasn't National Health then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that a big expense?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I don't know. I - I wouldn't know you see would I. And I never enquired what - what the cost of that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your parents have many friends outside of relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh just the usual neighbours
, yes. Very friendly with neighbours - faming neighbours. In fact they helped each other in those days. Harvest time they all - all clubbed in and - if you'd got a field today to be carried they - everybody would go and help and they'd come and help you w
h
en yours came along you see. There was three farmers actually that shared - shared a machine to cut the corn with and they shared the horses in so much that - they'd got three horses on each farm you see, and - they worked them then - the full day from as
 soon as it was dry in the morning until they could go home at night you see and just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were they all under the Bigadon Estate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But it wasn't like a little co-operative or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. No, it was just neighbour
ly - help, that's all. Neighbourly help. And of course we got help from them you see for the harvest, because you've got to remember - that everything had to be done with a - pitchfork in those days you know, there was nothing else, and - the men that use
d
 to work on the line, what they called packers, who maintained the line, they used to come and help - practically every farmer had joined the line in time, if he'd got a field of hay to take up this afternoon they'd come after they left work at five o'clo
c
k and they'd work 'til ten. And they didn't want any money. All they wanted was some cider and some - bread and cheese. And they'd expect some cider during the summer. When they were working on the line, and there were places where they used to leave the 
gallon jar and they knew where to pick it up. And that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And what would they do the rest of the time? Apart from harvest or summertime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well they'd got their gardens you see and - one used to come and cut the grass in the - in the - in t
he front garden for my mother and - with a - we had to cut it with a scythe you know, I mean lawnmowers were unheard of in those days. And - they did the vegetable garden you see and - they - they just mucked in together, then they expected to have - a fr
ee supply of swede turnips all the winter and - grow some potatoes in the field, which they were charged nothing for. You see, it was quite a - quite a different set up altogether than it is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Someone was telling me about dealing in eggs instead of money, almost a barter system, do you know anything about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - you see, these butchers and roundsmen that used to go around calling on farms and cottages used to take rabbits in l}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 eu of some meat. And visa versa, they'd take eggs you see, and there wouldn't be any money changed. They'd take the eggs and you'd hav}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 e so much meat for it you see. Q}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
uite a lot of that was done. And you were talking about entertainment some time ago, we used to have an old man that had a - a peg leg, with a - hand 
organ on - this - used to stand on a stick and a monkey on top and he used to come to that farm three times a year and play all the things outside you know and - mother used to take him out some bread and cheese and some tea and cider if he wanted it, and
 we used kids used to put a penny in the box and he used to go right around the neighbourhood. Yes. I can remember him quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He came back every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Two or three times a year he'd come, two or three times a year. I forget his name now, we 
used to know him. Great excitement when we saw him coming. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 He made his living that way did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, I suppose so. I suppose so. Went to the Union I expect you know to sleep. In those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What was the Union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh the Poor Law 
Institution you see, which is Broomborough hospital at Dartmouth now. That was the Union there you see. Run by - the Guardians of the - all the parishes around. And when a man was - destitute he went in there, but he had to work before he went away next m
orning for his night's sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did they allow people like travel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ers to come in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Even though they were working all the time singing and playing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - that - they'd got nowhere to sleep you see, they were just like - well,
 look at the tramps there were in those days, I mean in the summer they slept out beside the hedge, they didn't want to go in the Union 'cos if they did they knew they had to work next morning. But if they slept out by the hedge or in somebody's shed or a
 nice haystack that's where they went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have people coming round asking for night's kip in the haystack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, they didn't ask, you just found them there. Well you do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What was the attitude towards it, did your father mind finding a tramp in the haystack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well no, because they were looked upon as harmless you see, old - poor old fellow, he - give him a cup of tea and send him on the road you now. And they had their signs, they knew where to go where they wouldn't - where the
y did - weren't wanted. Some people gave 'em something and then you were told perhaps you were encouraging them, but - if you'd got any heart at all you can't see a man in the morning with no breakfast can you when you've had one. You see, that was the sp
irit in the country in those days. Mind there were old bogies about them of course but we never had any trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember people coming from one part of the country to do a bit of work and then move on again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. You see we - we were w
ell fitted up with labour. That - that occasion didn't arise but that - probably that did happen. But I know one farmer who lives - close to - a main road, and he got a lot of these - walking fellows in you see, after cider. That's all they wanted. They w
a
nted cider you see. And - he had two growing up boys and they saw how much cider was going out of the - place every - week, with these roadies as we called them you see, and he - sent one of the sons into Totones when he went to market and he told him to 
g
o in and buy two hand saws. And they cost half a crown the pair. And he brought them back, hung them inside his cellar door. And he said, now when they come again asking for cider, take out the saws and give them one each, there's the wheelbarrow, go up t
here and fill that with sawn logs, that length to go in our grate, and then they can have some cider. Didn't have many call after that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 These people didn't want to work for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. He didn't have many call after that. See they tell each other. But I remember that quite well when I was a kid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How would these people survive if they didn't to any work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well they went to the poor law institutions you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Then they'd have to work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Ah yes, well that's why they didn
't like going there 'cos they had to work for their sleep and their meal, I suppose they gave 'em a meal, I don't know. My father was a member of the Board of Guardians for Totnes Rural Council which I am a member of now. And then they had overseers in th
ose days you see in the parishes. They had - they had to collect the rates - from everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So these Poor Law things were supported on the rates were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of conditions were there in these workhouses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well I never went but - I understand they were - they were reasonable, they had a dry bed and - they gave 'em a bit of breakfast I suppose, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any people in Buckfastleigh who had to go there or was it mainly these trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3564036\charrsid2384185 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 lers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I
 would say it was people that - lived on the roads, you see there was a terrible depression wasn't there. You see, there was a depression wasn't there, I mean we were inundated with 'em down here after the first war. You see, they built those two by-passe
s
 at Buckfastleigh with labour down from Wales. For the unemployment. That was all done by hand. And look at the time it's taking them to do the one at Ashburton with all the machines they've got, when you realize that was all done when they done - in 1923
/
4, along then you see after the first war and that was all done by hand, the whole thing. And my uncle was a county surveyor and he constructed those two by-passes at Ashburton. Yes. They hadn't got bulldozers you know and - all this then, it was all - ha
rd slog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were a lot of people going off the land in these days, there was an agricultural depression about the late nineteenth century wasn't there?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Well I don't know - all I can remember is there was always plenty of - you see in the villa
ges and parishes similar to this the son went on the farm where his father was and - so it went on you see, and - and that's how it went on. But - you sed the whole thing is changed now, that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you find that your father and mother shared the same friends by and large?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, by and large. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 None other than relations that I know of you know. They weren't all relations, she had a lot of friends in Buckfastleigh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say your father had one or two farmer friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. They were all neighbourly around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose your father had more in common with some of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, of course you do. Yes, you see, you get - you naturally like some better than others I mean th
at's only natural isn't it. But generally speaking they were a very friendly crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When people came round would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, I mean to say the - you see - it - it was not - say they'd come a great distance b
ut it's the time it had taken them to get there, and would get back. You see - if you were only four miles away well you had - it was going to take you - however you can a good half an hour I mean, a bit more than that you see. If you came on a bicycle or
 
if you had a horse to ride you see. And there was always - a drink or - what was going you see. And if anybody came - just before midday meal they'd be invited in to have some of it. Didn't - they didn't always take it but they'd always be asked if they w
e
re neighbours you see. And people that used to come and do business in those days used to have something in the house. You see, travellers - and people selling - cattle foods and - or buying your - buying your wool, buying your apples to go away you see, 
they - it was quite a personal contact with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often would they come up for your wool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh only once a year. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you ever have any contact with the Hamblyns outside of that, would they have special fetes or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Not where we were. Not where we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you say then that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or your father's friends or both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh principally business. Principally. Outside the family. Yes, principally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When friends came would they call in casually or would they have an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well that would depend on whether you'd asked them to come. To a special meal. But if they came casually well they had to take pot luck. You see, you'd always ask them if they
'd like a drink and what they wanted to drink was cider. I mean that's what they lived on around here you see, that was the thing, there wasn't beer. I you wanted you went in a - into the town, got it in the pubs you see. But you see you have to realize t
h
at cider was three ha'pence a pint in those days. You see. A man that worked for me - when I went on business on my own in 1928, he went to Buckfastleigh on a Saturday night with a shilling in his pocket. And he came home with some change. And he had all 
t
he beer he could carry inside him. And a clay pipe and enough tobacco to last him the week. They gave the pipes you know then. If you bought tobacco you could buy a half ounce of baccy, I forget, about tuppence ha'penny wasn't it, something like that, and
 beer was about penny a pint or something like that you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They gave the pipes away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh Yes, gave a clay pipe with - in - in some places. Not all perhaps but - a lot of shops would give a clay pipe when you bought some tobacco. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So everyone sort of helped each other really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. That's it - that was just it you see. But then you see when the man went in the pub and had his drink if he was fairly regular and - the landlord would say, well there you are you haven't had a nic
e free pipe for a long time. Oh all right, I'll ask the boss and they'd take him too perhaps the next Saturday night and well he'd have a pint of beer you see, that was it. That's how they lived you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When neighbours came round would they just cal in casually as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. But not to make a proper call, they were there for some reason. You know, they'd come for a reason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 On the whole would people be there because they'd told you in advance they were coming?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Ah well, now that woul
d be a special invitation you see, but you din't know when the traveller was coming - but you knew roughly when the traveler would come. 'Cos there again he didn't go all round miles in one day in a motor car you know, he made about three or four calls, t
hat's all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Being on a farm you have to know when people are coming in a way otherwise you might be way out in the fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well mother was always in the house you see and there always seemed to be something to put on the table if they wanted it. 
You see - they used to buy a big joint of meat then on a Friday - on - on a - on a Friday, I mean they buy eight or ten pounds of bee in one - one lump you see, and that was it. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you always have relatives round weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Not always. Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often would you say your parents went out visiting friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well, that's hard to say. Hard to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That would depend on the season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. All sorts of things you see. That's hard to say. They went out w
hen they want to go out. But it was an effort to go very far. You see, because of transport.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When your parents got together with their friends or neighbours they played cards and odds and ends like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They didn't have musical evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Some - some sections of our family did, I had an uncle who was - had eight daughters and they - the whole choir of the church in the village that they lived in consisted of his eight daughters and himself and his wife played the organ. Now they w
ere musical. And if you went there to a Christmas party, any time around the Christmas, all you did was sing all night after you'd had something to eat, they - they were real musical people you see. But we weren't like that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you say you sang hymns round the piano, who would be there, just the family and the assistant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Ourselves. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You wouldn't have invitations sent out for other people to come round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. But this thing with the - this other uncle, they used to ha
ve these glee evenings they used to call them you see. And not only hymns, they used to sing all sorts of things, you know, with choruses to them, everybody joined in you see. But they were a very musical family you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Many people divide society in
to different social classes or groups, before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, yes, to a certain extent they did, there's no doubt about that I mean, let's face it. You see, the landlord and his associates
 - didn't mix socially with the tenants, as far as we were concerned. And the workers that worked for all the farmers didn't mix socially with the farmers. Except - they were given food in leiu of money for work they did. But they wouldn't mix socially if
 
you know what I mean. But you see if you went in a pub and there's a couple of your men were in there well you'd naturally give them a drink, well that still happens today. But it's only because you happen to meet them in the pub. But when you get - villa
ge life such as - garden shows and sports and fetes, well then of course they're absolutely mixed together. The whole three. The tope, the middle and the bottom, if you like to call it that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often did they have fetes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh once a year. They always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 That would be in the summer would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Garden shows you see and fetes and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have anything to do with helping with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well no, we weren't old enough you see at sixteen. You see that happened after - after 
- between the two wars when I was interested in that in this parish. You see that was later on altogether. Oh yes, we had a football team, I played football for the local team here in the village. And my brother played cricket you see, we - we mixed in on
 that, and then you see you got - all sections of the community were mixedup in that. Didn't matter who you were, what you were, you all had the same chance you see. There wasn't any class distinction at all - in that. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But otherwise without people making a point of it it was just the way things were, that different people kept themselves to themselves?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well you see if you wanted to see - if you wanted to see your landlord about something special you - you would go there - rather sub
dued and you'd have to ask if you could see him. You couldn't go up and knock at the door and say I want to see you. You see, you had to go through the channels to get hold of the fellow to start with you see. And they would come and see you by appointmen
t
 at the farm when they came to discuss - rents or whatnot, repairs, they - they'd make an appointment, they were coming with their agent at a certain time. And they expected you to be there to meet them - to discuss the business and when they'd finished t
hey'd go. They may have a cup of tea before they go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say you used to go up there to children\rquote s parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, and that was all sections of the community, I mean - coachmen's children and gardeners children and farmers children and their own c
hildren all mixed together. In those parties, there was no class distinction whatsoever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any things like parties for the farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well the same thing applied, but there again, the workers children wouldn't be in those parties. Unless 
they - in - in a case as ours were they were because you see they'd been with us so long. You see, the kids, they were brought up like we - with us, I mean, we knew them as we knew our brothers and sisters. They were in the cottages quite close to where w
e lived you see. And when I tell you one is still down with my brother working now and he's about eight years younger than me, that's all. Oh you see we've been brought up together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say this is probably normal around Devon as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I sup
pose it is in the country districts. I can only speak for our own - you know, but - men did stay on farms for years and years, well they stayed then 'til they were too old to do anything, let's face it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would you say the different classes were then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 The landlords and the farmers and the workers. That's all - you can only divide it in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, you respected your - your respected your 
elders in any case no matter where the came from. And - you were taught to speak to people no matter where they came from in the same sort of way, approach them in the same way. And you would respect, as I told you before I think, - the parson and the doc
t
or, and - the bank manager and all that, my grandfather used to take his hat off before he'd even go inside the bank. Leave it out on the step, I've been with him - heaps times and seen him do that. Oh yes, you see, there was more respect altogether in th
ose days for everything. It's so different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of group would they belong to, the doctors and bank managers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh they'd be a bit above farmers. Well they thought they were at any case, in those days, they thought they were a bit above farme
rs. You see, farmers were considered themselves a bit above shopkeepers. You see, it went along in - in that sort of line you see. They thought they were in a - a different category altogether. But - but that - gradually died out you see, depended on a ma
n's luck didn't it. If he made a lot of money he soon got in with the upper gang, he was accepted you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think there was much moving from one group to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not a lot. Not a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You sometimes hear of people moving down the social scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well of course you do, of course you do, you see - well we mustn't go into that now, because this is my trouble about education you see, that's what I said this was all going to happen, it's happened hasn't it. Nobody wants to do the work. 
See if you're going to teach everybody to be so clever that they can do the writing whose going to do the working. That's what we're up against today. You've got to be fair about that you know. Once they take these children away from our village schools w
h
en they were eleven years old they don't come back into the village anymore and go on the farms to work or do anything local, they're gone. And there's where you've got your trouble of too many in the towns with nothing to do. But they won't come back and
 
work on the land as they - as they - as their grandfathers did. They think you see, it's - it's - it's beneath them to do that because they've been to college or been to university, whatever you like you see. And that is the trouble. See, we've got it her
e
, there's a shortage of farm workers generally speaking. Because the sons have not taken on their fathers jobs. And I suppose - we've got a case in our own village where the father was - going every day, cracking stones beside the road with a hammer, knee
l
ing on a bag, I've seen him. He had three sons, and a daughter. The daughter's been a schoolteacher al her life, she's retired. One son is a surveyor up in Sussex or Surrey, another one is a manager in one of them departments at Dartington Hall and the ot
h
er one has got a damned good job in Newton Abbot. Well who's going to crack the stones? You see, if the top - boy, that's got independent means, doesn't get through with his exams and pass so as he can get a job up there is he coming down to take the plac
e of the ones that were down there that have gone up on top? Then you've unbalanced the whole thing haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you think in the times we're talking about there was much more of a social balance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, of course there was. Of course there w
as. Mind, I think we are suffering from the sins of our forefathers to a great extent. In underpaying people. Think they had a very hard life then. I agree with you on that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think they realize it though, they had a hard life but they were happy in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
They were happier. That's the point you see. - Now the trouble is today nobody knows what they want do they, I mean let's face it. You see, they can't all be - doing these - top technical jobs can they. And yet it seems to be a short
age of skilled people doesn't there. Look at the papers every day. That are advertising, that's what I don't understand. With all these people that have had all this education, I - I don't understand it all, with all these unemployed and yet you see - you
 
look at the Mail. They have one day a week where they put in all these adverts, well it's all for technical jobs and they don't seem to be able to get 'em, well why not, where are they. I suppose they don't want the work, that's - that - that's - that's t
he middle and both ends of it to me. I think it's very serious for the country as a whole, I mean, I don't know what's going to happen. I really don't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was your sister ever told to curtsey? Or you to touch your cap or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. Only when you saw the King - or Queen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Down here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Out on the middle of Dartmoor in 1912. When they had some races out there and - the then George V I suppose, yes. Is that right? Came there with Alex
andra, they were; married and he was the Prince of Wales. And they came to the - point-to-point out there with a - two white horses and a carriage and pair and they stayed at the Duchy Palace the Prince had. And then you had to curtsey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well yes, up to a point they did, I mean - the workmen all addressed my father ass sir. And every other person. I mean, all other farms did the same thing. It wasn't an exceptional case in any of that. And in a lot of cases instead of sir it was master.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about your mother, what would she be called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh Mrs Warren. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Who would be considered the most important people in the district, the parson and the landlords and people like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. We did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Why were they considered so important do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well you see it was the way we were brought up to respect - a landlord, because he was the squire and he owned everything around him. And - you see - the farm th
at - we had in particular belonged to him and he was looked upon as the - as the squire of the area around, as - in many other instances, I mean he wasn't an exceptional one. And we were always - expected to - respect the parson. And - lift your hat to hi
m - cap to him when you met him and - address him as sir.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was the parson a local man or was he from somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 From Buckfastleigh. Buckfastleigh was our parish you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But what about the actual man, the parson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh didn't matter who the man was, he was the parson.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I wondered whether he was from Buckfastleigh or whether he came from somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I don't know where he came from, this - in particular - that particular time I forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh now - no - no distinction in - in - no distinction in position in any shape or form. There were a lot of - ordinary - working people that went to church in addition to - landlords and - people like that. And some of the landlords went to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So there wasn't any sort of distinction between who went to church and who went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. Oh no, no, no. No. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say that people kept themselves to themselves in many ways, so that shopkeepers wouldn't mix with the bankers or the doctors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh no, I didn't say that, I said you see that it was difficult - when you were living in the country to become - very - friendly with people who lived in towns because there was the - there was the tran
sport problem. You see, you didn't see them. And if they had to come to you it was - they either had to have some form of conveyance or it was a long way to walk. They did, some of them but not - generally - speaking. But they were quite on the same socia
l level. As farmers. Exactly. Butchers, all the lot of them. No difference in that at all. Just - friends, business friends, that's what you could call them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you find where you lived all the people in the working class had the same standard of livi
ng of were there some different groups among the working class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well you see that applies to all - all - sections of community doesn't it, whether they're thrifty or - and there are the unthrifty and of course we had them. You had some of both. Some
 would never have any money however much you gave 'em and others would get money somehow by saving it and working harder, I mean you always get that don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Can you remember any one family in particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Very poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Very poor or very thrifty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No, not - not really, I mean - I don't think there were any real poor in Buckfastleigh except one or two families as I say - who the father didn't want to work and he wouldn't work, well I mean you get that amongst a community don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What would happen to that family then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well he just used to live on his wits I suppose, I - I wouldn't know. The children went to school you see, it was a free school. And - he earned a living in various ways, perhaps if you - were on about the other day, did a bit of poaching, I don't know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would they get any help from the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, oh yes, they did, they - they - they did, that's what the Board of Guardians were for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say your father was on the Board of Guardians?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes, he was on for the Totnes Rural for years. And when they got a - a very bad case I imagine they applied to them for relief. And I suppose they got some, I was too young to know what they got or anything about it, I don't remember that part of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any families who were thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, of course there were. Of course there. The odd ones. Still get them now don't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was there some kind of distinction between craftsmen and labourers do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. Not to my knowledge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think that one group would feel superior to the rest or was it just sort of unstated?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, I don't think if you take tradesmen generally speaking, a mason or a carpenter - I don't think he th
ought any less of a man that - was labourer to him, than he did of a - of his - of his next mason, I - I mean they all had to work together as they do today. I suppose that - a carpenter considers himself a little better standing than an ordinary labourer
 but - in some cases a labourer gets as much money today as the - as the craftsmen doesn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What about in those days though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I don't know you see, I mean would I up to sixteen, I wouldn't know you see what it was at all. I - I couldn't te
ll you on that - score.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people in different group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, I think so. Oh yes, they'd got no - naturally there was a few people they disliked, well that always happens doesn't it. But not
hing - that ever worried us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, I don't think she did. We had one neighbouring farmer who we all feared. Because he used to drink far too much and - when we were wa
lking, either home from school or going - into the village he'd drive by on a - very wet and muddy day, the roads hadn't got tarmac on 'em then you know, and splash us all over because he was so tight he didn't know what he was doing, we were always warne
d - if we heard him coming to get a gateway, get out of the way because he's just as likely to drive over you as not, but - he didn't drive over us but he thought nothing of tipping his cart over. Sticking the horse back again and going on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How was his farm all this time, did he manage to keep going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well he had two sons. Yes. But you see, you get that today don't you. I mean you get the man that drinks too much today I mean, he's - he's - he's a menace on the road isn't he with the motor car. The
 same thing, well this man was a menace with a trap, a horse and trap and he - could be, you know, that's it. They were few and far between but that's - you mentioned you know - was there anybody that - we feared, well that was the - that was one person w
e did fear. When we were kids.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, quite a lot. Quite a lot. And a few of them have - have lasted up to - the last eight or ten years, but they're fast going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Why was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well they were you see, I suppose they had money and they used the money in a sensible way and looked after people that wanted money and - they owned a bit of - properly as a rule and - they were looked upon as a real lady or a real gentle
man because of their attitude towards the rest of the people in general, that's only - the only reason. You see, the Victorian age is fast disappearing, I mean - around in our area here we've lost three, well over eighty, which continued - most of their l
i
fe in - in living in the Victorian age. They - they lived a very - rather secluded type of life and were very particular - about how they lived and - they kept a butler or - or - or a footman right up to - right up to the end and expected the service that
 they got when they were - twenty-five I suppose. Seventy or eighty years ago you see, well - they've gone, they're going. There's very few left round here. Very few.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where do you think they've all gone to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh they died, I mean, they've gone you see, they've gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was there any policemen around Buckfastleigh?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Yes. Oh yes. We were policed better then than we are now. Yes, they had two regular policemen at Buckfastleigh. And they used to come around and first the farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh that's how they found out things. That is one of our grudges today. With the Panda cars, they fly though here two or three times a week, they don't stop to speak to anybody. Well if you've got a message to give 'em or they want to find out some info
rmation we say this is the place to get it. I mean they could do it by - just in the way of - of talking, did you see so and so happen yesterday, did you see anybody this way or something, but - you see, that - that is one of the things we are complaining
 
about, to the - to the - to the Chief Constable, we - we had a - a discussion on this - in the council and we were asked our opinion - of the Panda car versus the length of - the - the resident policeman, which - they're all gone now you see. And we say, 
w
e don't object to the - Panda car system, but - let the man stop when he comes to the village. Perhaps at the shop, or at the pub, and just get out and walk around and if he sees somebody - just pass the time of the day and - if he wants some information 
that's where he's going to get it from. You see - we feel the personal touch has been lost with the policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were the policemen liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. And of course when we were small kids we stood in - we stood - we were frightened of them when they c
ame along, the policeman's coming you know, well - look out. You see, but if you'd done anything wrong they clipped you over the ear and give you a good - smack across the backside and that would be that, you wouldn't hear anything more about it, everybod
y
 was happy. But - you see - I don't know why it's gone this way but it has hasn't it. I was in the special police myself from 1926 up to 1950 - '60. I did duty in the general strike in 1926. Then on the line down here. What we were supposed to be doing I 
don't know but we went down there eve night. Walked up and down, just to see I suppose nobody even carried the lines away, I don't know - what - what they wanted but we were there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were there any nicknames for policemen can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - 
yes, but not - not outside - I mean, when I was in the special police right through the war you see we were - very much connected with the regulars. We - we were almost - accepted as in - in with them, and we had nicknames for various people then but not 
- any special nickname for a special policeman anywhere you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you were naughty did your mother ever say I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. But a lot of families did. But I don't think she - see, my mother - looked at the in the wrong way to bring
 a child up because it puts fear into you. She wanted you to respect the policeman. Not to run away from him because he was coming. And I think that is where a lot of your trouble started - about the police, a policeman's coming you see, if you don't beha
v
e he'll do so and so to you, well of course it's wrong. And I think that's where this - sort of - break between the general public and the policeman started with the kids. You see, we were brought up to - respect the policeman and if we were in trouble to
 go to him. He was the man to go to if you were in trouble.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of trouble, lost your way or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - anything, yes, well you did get lost I mean as they do now because if a child gets lost now they give it out over a loudspeaker, 
there were no loudspeakers then, they just had to go round until they could find it. If you went to a race-meeting or anything and you got lost well - you'd have to - they'd have to shout to you, there was no loudspeakers to notify that a kid was in - suc
h
 and such a place waiting for its parents. It was much harder in those days. But you see if you found a policeman and told him he'd take you to where you wanted to go. And if he was your local policeman, he - he knew you and you knew him. And you had conf
idence that he would look after you and take you to where you wanted to go you see. It's - it's - it's a great pity that I feel, but there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You were talking about these men who used to come round and you'd find them asleep in the haystack or th
e hedge, did you ever have any the tramp people, did you ever get gypsies coming round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, when - well this is not - not in this time mind, this is after that. After the age of sixteen. But since we've been farming up at the top of the hill up t
here we had a gipsy and his wife and family used to come - once a year with a pony and trap and - they'd put up a tent - up in a bit of a - sheltered spot in an old \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 very little used and he used to cut wood and make clothes pegs. And - and take 
them off and of course - we always had a mistrust his horse was in the field when you were in bed eating your grass, but it was difficult to catch them, but - they didn't do any other damage, and there again, they - you see - gypsies are exactly the same 
a
s I said about the other, if you're on good terms with them they won't do you any harm. They never did us any harm. I had some gypsies come to me once to buying scrap iron - just before the second war. And - when he was there going around seeing what was 
l
aying around I happened to notice he'd lost his little finger. Well he agreed to pay me - I think it was two pounds for this - what he was going to collect up and - they'd come and get it - take some off today, it's the old story you see, I was muggings. 
O
h we'll take a little with us today, we'll come back and collect the rest you see, we'll give you ten bob. When we come back you shall have the other - thirty shillings you see, so - somebody said, oh you've seen that, you've had that, you see, well they 
d
id come back but they came back and took the rest without they didn't see me, it went. Well now what I'm coming to is this, that there was a family of gypsies who lived - at the top end of this parish in by the A38, and - I used to go and take those peopl
e
 down to vote at Parliamentary elections - they couldn't read or write, the old girl couldn't, and I used to take her in and the - returning officer made a mark for her, any rate - I happened to say to her one day, look - I had so and so came in not so lo
n
g ago and - told them exactly as I've told you, and I said - then she said, can you tell me who it was? I said, he hadn't got any - finger on his left hand, little finger. Oh, she said, thank you. I'll see you get your thirty bob and I got it. Yes. I got 
it. Yes. So you see - that - that's it you see, if - if - if you - I know they're - they're a bit of a nuisance some places, but gypsies -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You can't remember much about gypsies before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember anything about whether there was anyone in the district whom people disapproved of very strongly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well I don't know about disapproving but there were a couple of old men - than used to pass down - the same lane as we went to go to Buckfastleigh who we were rather frightened o
f as kids but - I don't think that - there was any harm in them. Got to remember my sister and I were walking down a road just before five with just a candle lantern and these two - old people used to come scraping along going home from work but we used t
o be a bit scared of them but they never did nothing wrong to us, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever tell your parents about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh they knew, everybody knew them. Yes, they knew them. I could give you their names and - but - and their descendants are still livi
ng in Buckfastleigh, but they were the rough type you see, one - had been a sailor in the good old sailing days and he was a bit rough but - they never interfered with us but we were scared of 'em that's all, as kids. Yes, you see, no other reason.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Your parents didn't say to watch out for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well they always used to say don't stop talking to them, come along you know, and - and I think they respected that. These men, because they knew. There were other kids besides us, but we were a bit frigh
tened of them you see. You got them in every parts, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You don't remember anyone specifically?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You don't know anything about rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you think the policeman treated the people fairly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 O
h very. Very. Yes. Except for one or two exceptions, the village people and towns, small town people were very sorry when a policeman was moved. Which they were as they are today. You'd get some, they'd say, but not a lot, but very good job he's gone, but
 - generally speaking I tell you they were looked up to. By everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were they generally local people or would they come here from somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, they moved just like they do now, you may get a man from North Devon, you may get a man f
rom - Exmouth or anywhere, posted to Buckfastleigh you see. They were under a superintendent in Totnes in those days you see and they had an area right around them, they - you've seen it - well you see the changes don't you know in the paper now and again
, that so and so's transferred from so and so and they did exactly the same then. Exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where would they live, in the town itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh we had a police house. Had a police house in - right in the town there. Ordinary cottage in a row of cottages
 where all people lived you see. Then - well that doesn't matter as far as now but now of course they've got a council house up on - right on the A38, the same thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well yes, but it was always a struggle. No doubt about that. In agriculture as it is today. You hear the programmes on - on television. We had a very interesting one on Peninsular now only a few nights ago and - you see, there's a false impre
ssion with townspeople versus country people, farmers in particular, they seem to think that they're living on a bed of roses but they're not you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What did you think about this when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well I realized that it was going to mean
 a lot of hard work but you see I never had any opportunity - to think about anything else. That was it. Except when I went in the services and then I wondered whether I should come home or not you see. But - I was wanted home and - that was that you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you being the eldest one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Exactly. Exactly, yes that was the point you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What difference would it make to the family when your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh very little. It would still go on exactly the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you ever fill in when you were still at school if he was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well I couldn't be necessary you see if you'd got three men working for you you see, you'd still have to come and do your - odd jobs evenings and - and - no, it didn't affect it very much. I remember he met
 with a very bad accident with a saw, and cut his hand rather badly right across the top of the knuckles, well he didn't - couldn't use that hand for - probably six weeks, it turned septic, it was - a nasty old business but it went on exactly the same. - 
Of course he was missed, but there you are. That was it. It had to go on, you see, you couldn't stop, you can't stop a farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you get any help from the Guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, not in that respect, no, you - you may get an extra - a - a
 neighbour would send a man perhaps to help with - if you had something special to do on a special day and you were short because he was ill - he was indisposed, all right, we'll send a man up and help you. And that's how - how things were worked with the
se smaller type of farms you see. You helped each other, neighbourly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You didn't get any sort of help from the landlord when that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No financial assistance of anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You did a year's full time work before you went in the services didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you get paid for helping on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, but not a fixed rate. Got money for it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What exactly did you do, when you were just helping around, the odd jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well it's diffic
ult to explain you see, I mean, it - it's part of - of - it's part of the daily routine of - of any farm, in those days, when there were no machines you see, you had your horses to see to. And the cows had to be milked, you had a lot of calves you were re
a
ring, they had to be fed with milk and - and bedded down and - you see, there was a certain - at certain times of the year there was a certain set pattern of jobs that had to bed one. You see, and they had to be done mornings and evenings. Much lighter yo
u see in the summer you see than in the winter when everything was indoors, and had to be - fed with hay and whatever - whatnot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How much would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh well that would depend how much you found wasn't done when you got there. You'd say
, oh look they haven't been fed over on that side now, you go and do them will you? Right, well you'd do it and then - perhaps the next day they'd done them. And they didn't - they'd say, oh everything's finished tonight, we're early. Right, well off they
 go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What age do you think you would be when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh about nine or ten. Yes, about nine or ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What time of day would you start, did you work before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, from about half an hour you had your little dutie
s to do, not a lot but you had a little to do and you had a little to do when you came home. And - I mean you came home and you changed your clothes and put on your - what they call rough clothes that you wore you wouldn't wear your school clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did the hours increase as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes. Well not really because the work didn't increase you see. Just the same - it was the same routine. I mean, at one time of year you had more calves to feed than you did another, of course it just depended
 you see, there's no hard and fast rule on it of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you'd have your school hours which would be regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, quite.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You didn't go to school on Saturdays did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, Saturday morning. Yes. Saturday mid-days and Wednesday m
id-days. You see. They made us go - they made us go the six days. Which we thought at the time was crazy. But there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you do more work on a Saturday afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 On the Saturday - Saturday afternoon you'd do - well you'd do what you h
ad - Saturday afternoon there was always work to do if you liked to go out and do it you see. And being keen on it you did it. You weren't actually forced to do it you see. But I can remember when I loved to go home and take one horse or two horses and go
 up in a field and do some work, harrowing away and whatever was going on you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And it would depend on the season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Exactly. Exactly you see, but of course they didn't much about with the clocks like they do now. We had one time all the year ro
und. But - that made a lot of difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you help with any of the essentials on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, you'd do exactly the same. In fact very often you see as you got older one of the men needn't come tomorrow, you can do it with the other on
e. And then the next week the other one can have the Sunday you see. It - it just worked in. It just worked in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well that didn't come into it you see. It wasn't the case of that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Have you any idea what you'd be paid during this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No. I forget. I forget. But I told you a pound was a lot of money in those days, well if you were given a pound perhaps once a fortnight you thought you were pretty well off - and being kept you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would this be in addition to your pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
It would be in addition to the money you had when you were going to school as pocket money, yes. For the extra work you'd done you see. And you see if you were going anywhere and - there was a train fare t
o pay well you'd be given the money, there, there's your train fare, you see, that's because you've been helping - to get that money. You see what I mean, you see, that was it, it was worked in that way. There was no hard and fast rule about how much you 
were going to have and how many hours you were going to work, and then if you wanted to have half a day off you just said, well. I want to go to so and so tomorrow afternoon, and you could go.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 This is when you started full time is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yo
u see, but there was no fixed thing about finishing on Saturday at a certain hour or - on Sunday, but if you said, look I want to go to so and so - any afternoon or any evening or any morning you said you wanted to go all day, yes, all right, if you want 
to go go. Nothing was said.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So it was very sort of easy going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well exactly, yes, it was - it was a form of life you see. Quite different to today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But you'd have to get up, the early morning tasks would have to be done, like the cows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
That's got to be done twice, if you weren't there somebody else had to do it you see but you see when - when - when they wanted to be off you had to do it then and you had double do. But you didn't say anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But I mean you'd have to get up every morning quite early?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There was no question of lying in or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 We didn't want to. Never thought about it you see, never thought - not up to that age at any rate you see, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever have any other part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So when you were sixteen you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you did this one year full time on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes. Well bit more than one year, year and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of wage would you get then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well no, it was exactly the same as it was before. If you wanted a pound you asked for it. And you had it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Being the oldest son you'd have a different sort of relationship than the ordinary sort of farm worker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well he was on a fixed rate. And fixed hours you see. It was quite different. You couldn't compare us at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You'd be the embryonic boss really wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well yes, exactly, as you got older, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And since the first world war you've been farming all your life have you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Up to 1965.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you ever have preferred any other kind of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Hard to say. Very hard. I sometimes wonder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What might you have done otherwise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, you see - I had an opportunity to stay on in the services. With pretty
 good prospects after doing about two and a half years. They asked me to stay on actually. And as I walked out of the barracks to come home when I was discharged - a man tapped me on the shoulder outside Woolwich Grand Depot and said, where are you going?
 
I said home to my home. He said, look if everything's all right inside come down with me you can go straight in the mounted police. You see. Well it makes you think you see. Now had I done that - in 1922 - I could have done twenty-one years in the police 
and I could still gone out and gone farming after with a pension behind me, if I had any luck the only snag I see that was - you'd have been called back to London for the second world war and that wasn't very healthy was it. There you are you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You say this happened in 1922?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes, when I came out from the services. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Then first war ended in 1918 didn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 '18. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You left four years after that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well we were out Far - out in Far East in Mesopotamia then you see. We were still on active service right up to '21. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever to do any apprenticeship or training period?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. There was no such thing in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was there any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes I think there were, there were - yes, I thi
nk there were - there were workers - farm worker unions, I think they - yes, they'd started hadn't they, they had a - real set-up didn't they in 1874 or something or other, there was a - they went on strike I believe didn't they and formed a union, a man 
f
rom Cornwall I think formed these - agricultural workers - well it was from the West Country anyway. Yes, I think - I think there were, I think they were formed before that. But as far as I know the men that we had took no interest in unions at all. It wa
s never mentioned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How about yourself, was there any professional organization?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
There was the National Farmers Union. Of which my father was a member. But he was one of the founder members of that and I believe that started in about 1912. Just before the first world war. Maybe 1908.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What led him to join that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Well I suppose he thought it was a good idea you see to safeguard - well, farmers generally. He was always keen on more co-operation between farmers which you've never had which I 
think is a great mistake but - there again there's a great argument for and against that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 But it would be co-operation locally between different ones wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 There were amongst the smaller ones but the bigger ones rather thought themselves 
too big for - to be worried about the little ones you see. And that has gone all through hasn't it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was Rill a big farm, it looks a huge one from the road? Was it considered big in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Up there? Well they're all the same in this pa
rish you see, the - the church commissioners own four thousand acres here. And - in those days the farms ran - from two hundred to two hundred and fifty to three hundred acres. And they had those - that type of house and building on all of them. That hous
e
 was built in about - about a hundred years ago. Because the people that - went when I went there - his father was there before him, and the son that I relieved in 1928 was born - in - the old cottages down below there and taken up there as a small child 
into this new farm house. And - they - they're a hundred years old now, and there's three of them in this parish exactly the same design. And the others are a squarer type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They look almost Italian somehow don't they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - I don't know. Well t
hey've got a new one, the church built down here twenty-five years ago which I think is awful but there you are. It's all stone and - it's quite a substantial place. They've since sold it, the farm has been - thrown in with another one you see, that's wha
t they're doing, that's why that happened up there you see. That's a farm no more as a farm. It was divided and put with three other farms adjoining and - that became obsolete.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever join this National Union of Farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of activities would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh I was Chairman of the - Totnes branch in 1932 or 33.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What kind of things did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, meetings you see and - organizations and - of course it's got into quite a big thing as you kno
w now, it's quite different than it was then but we used to have an executive meeting at Exeter you see for the - Devon county branch and - and members from there served in London, the same principle as it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have any social activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, they had a - they have a - they have a dinner and a thing every year, annual dinner and - they used to run things to get money in those days, of course now the - the membership - fee is fantastic compared to when it started, I forget, it used to b
e about tuppence an acre or something like that now it's somewhere about five pounds an acre I believe, something like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Where did the idea come from, what part of the country did it start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - I - I suppose - I don't know, I reme
mber when my father started - and a few of them got together, and went to this first meeting and they formed a branch, I think they had branches up the country earlier than they did in the West Country, the West Country's usually behind with most things b
ut - they - they caught up in the end as the do. And of course there were benefits you see. They ran a mutual insurance company for one thing with far less premiums than - the ordinary tariff people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was that there straight away at the beginning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I think so. As long as I can remember there was one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different interests?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They have exactly the same, the - the employers were simply interested in the farm and all the work the
y were doing. In those days. That was it. Didn't matter what time of the day it was or what time of night, if he wanted them they'd come. You had a bas case of the cow carrying or anything you'd only got to - you had to go up and get 'em, that was the big
gest trouble, you hadn't got a phone to ring 'em up like you have now, and they'd come. That was it. They'd be annoyed if you didn't ask 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I suppose it was their life wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well exactly, you see, they were exactly like us you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 It's not like doing a job on a conveyor belt is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No. Oh no. Quite different you see. And you see we had to breed our own horses in those days, our work horses all had to be bred on the farm. Well then you had your mares to foal in - March, April tim
e, well the horseman was as keen on that as you sere, he was out every night watching to see when this - this foal was coming along you see, and - and they - they took an interest in it you see. - 'Cos they knew that they wanted that to replace another on
e in four or five years time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 So you didn't think there was any division of interest amongst workers themselves? From your experience in that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 They used to be - a lot of competition amongs}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1134495\charrsid2384185 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185  them - as to the crops that they grew. And the type of horses they had, and th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1134495\charrsid2384185 ey way they could turn their ho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 rses out and their wagons. There was competition. But it wasn't any grievance at all. You see, they were one competing against the other to have something better, they tried to grow - or helped to g
row a better field of roots than the next door neighbour, you see, and they'd go and talk about it in the pub on Sundays. What they'd got and what the others had got you see. There was more - you see, they - they - they were interested in it absolutely, t
hey were part of it you might say. Part of the - of - of the enterprise you see without any mistake. And this was pretty general. But whether it was the same as you get the other side of Ex}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1134495\charrsid2384185 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 ter further up I don't know. But it was down in the South West Part, around here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 On a farm would there be like a distinction between a trained craftsman and other workers, in an agricultural setting would that apply?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well no because you see in those days they were general farm workers. One would cart - would c
lass himself as a horseman and the other as a cowman, as they do now. But there was no difference, one would help the other. You see, when it was his - weekend off the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1134495\charrsid2384185 
 other one would do his and vice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185  versa, there was no - this is mine and that's yours, they - and they all helped each other you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Mine? No. No I don't think it did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 When you left school you continued to live at home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 I don't get that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 For instance would you - would they treat you more as an adult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh no, you were gradually growing up, you were - you - couldn't do some
thing until you were seventeen or something like that, you - you had to - toe the line I mean. But gradually grew up you see. And you weren't treated any different when you were on the farm than you were when you were going to school. Exactly the same set
 up. Yes, exactly. Didn't alter you see. You had one thing in view and that was all. To help all you could and get all you could out of it you see what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did it change your relationship with your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, none whatever. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Was Sunday spent any differently after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No, not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you take any interest in politics at all at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you vote in any general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Didn't have the vote until you were twenty-one did you, no I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever feel under any pressure from any one to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No. None whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 And you weren't a member of any political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You took no part in political activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
In the year and half between leaving school and going away did your social life change very much once you'd left school, did you keep the friends you were at school with for instance? Did they come over and see you still after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you be allowed to go out in the horse and trap on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes, you could go where you liked, Provided you made the arrangements, I mean, you didn't go - just walk out, you kn
ow. Oh yes, there was no restrictions at all. But then I had a bicycle, and then you see I was self-supporting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 You wouldn't be old enough to go in the pub would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Not then, no, they didn't do that. They didn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you go out in the evenings very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
Oh yes, you used to go - meet some other boys and probably some girls as well and go a ride on a bike, you know what they do. In summer well - probably you ride into Totnes or even Buckfastleigh, Ashburton. Newton Abbot if yo
u were energetic enough, eight miles there and back, but we did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you make any new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes, quite a lot I expect. You know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How would you meet new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well, by going as I told to - various towns or villages. And I 
- I - I played football for the village football team, well you see you keep on meeting new people then and you naturally get friendly with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 How often did you play then, once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well - roughly, yes. Roughly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 What position did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Centre half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 
No. Not - not - not really - you know, not - anything different, we were - friendly with quite a lot of fellows and girls and just - you know - never had any particular -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh yes. Yes, whenever you wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Would you have to ask beforehand or would you just bring them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Well there again you see, you - you're up against distances, you see, you can't compared it with pre
sent day. It's quite different you see, when you realize the nearest friends live a mile away, you see, it's easy today isn't it to jump in car, you see, they had to get back, you had to think about that when they come back with you and stay for half an h
o
ur and perhaps have a drink of some sort and there you are, a glass of milk was very - very free and easy in those days you see, and have a talk and then probably father would say, it's time you boys get off you know, it's nine o'clock, it'll be dark befo
re you get home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Did your parents expect to know where you were when you went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh they expected you to tell them where you'd been. And where you were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12395013 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Were you expected to be home at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7484565 DW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7236058\charrsid2384185 Oh we were told not to be too late. You see.
\par }}